INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(111,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>- The current process is inefficient with emails getting lost and tasks sitting pending</li><li>- Teams are using too many manual spreadsheets rather than leveraging Salesforce capabilities</li><li>- Recent standardization attempt with NP Digital''s process has not been effective</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><ul><li>- Modifying the "Primary Product Family" field would impact numerous automations and requires careful planning</li><li>- Technical assessment showed changes to existing fields would require removing them from all automations first</li><li>- Victoria discovered that changing field types would affect all versions and associations in Salesforce</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>- Victor to speak with AN to understand the ideal client handover process workflow</li><li>- Victoria to meet with developers to understand current automation dependencies</li><li>- Team to consider designing a new process from scratch rather than modifying existing one</li><li>- Project to be tackled after completing the Salesforce field mapping work</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',14,'2025-04-10 19:13:19.862227','2025-04-10 19:13:19.862227');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(112,'content','<ul><li><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong><ul><li>- Meta ads delivered a significant win with a new enterprise client that was completely net new</li><li>- Cost per lead at $51, showing improvement from L3M ($59)</li><li>- Paid channel performance is declining with cost per DC at $324 vs. historical average of $177</li><li>- Pacing for only 46 DCs from paid vs. target of 80 DCs needed to reach deal goals</li><li>- Intro call volume from paid ads has decreased by 77% while spend decreased by only 50%</li><li><br></li></ul></li><li><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong><ul><li>- Conversion API improvements are delivering better signals to Meta''s algorithm per Rafael</li><li>- Team debated whether landing pages vs. Meta forms impact quality, with the recent enterprise win supporting current approach</li><li>- Recent creatives using AI-generated content did not perform well and Rafael requested changes</li><li>- Economic uncertainty is likely affecting ad performance beyond what optimization can fix</li><li><br></li></ul></li><li><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong><ul><li>- Test duplicate campaign approach to increase spend without disrupting existing campaigns</li><li>- Rafael to create NPD-specific analysis to evaluate potential cost-sharing opportunities</li><li>- Remove AI-generated creative content and focus on service-related organic content</li><li>- Optimize for a target cost per DC of $300-350 while continuing to monitor performance</li></ul></li></ul><div>- Rafael to increase Meta Ads budget to $30K (from current $20K) with consideration for a further increase to $35K<br>- Sarah to discuss potential cost-sharing arrangements with NPD for Meta Ads based on recent success</div><ul><li>- Victor to continue analyzing conversion rate trends and identifying anomalies in the data</li><li>- Team to investigate if we need to adjust our offering mix (more paid/email vs. SEO) given economic conditions</li></ul><div><br></div>','WeeklySummary',15,'2025-04-10 19:13:19.977095','2025-04-10 19:27:24.712222');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(113,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>- The "Blitz" initiative (started March 11th) improved win rates from 11-15% to 20-27% during March</li><li>- April win rates are showing a decline (currently at 4-10%) likely due to economic uncertainty</li><li>- Total pitch held are pacing for 81 this month vs. 133 last month</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><ul><li>- Nick identified several deals that closed specifically due to leadership involvement</li><li>- Data analysis confirmed the "Blitz" strategy had significant impact, but sustainability is a concern</li><li>- Current market conditions are impacting buyer behavior with increased hesitation and decision delays</li><li>- Discovery call quality issues are affecting downstream pitch quality and conversion rates</li></ul><div><br><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>- Nick and Lindsay to create formal guidelines for when contracts should be sent (client verbal approval, decision maker engagement, specific timeline)</li><li>- Team to continue the "Blitz" strategy of leadership joining critical pitches and follow-ups</li><li>- Nick to implement stronger discovery call structure and coaching to address quality issues</li><li>- Lindsay and Nick to focus on examining and documenting effective exit questions to improve pitch outcomes</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',16,'2025-04-10 19:13:19.987170','2025-04-10 19:13:19.987170');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(114,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>- Quiz leads are recovering with 125 for the current week (likely to exceed previous week''s 214)</li><li>- "Let''s Grow Your Traffic" lead volume has declined from 19-21 per week to 12 L2W</li><li>- Email campaigns are underperforming with recent webinar emails generating only 4-5 DCs</li><li>- Conversion rates from DC to pitch have declined to 36% from historical 45%</li><li>- Organic channel maintained consistent DC volume at 129 vs. historical average of 138, but conversion rates dropped to 31% (vs. historical 52%)</li><li>- Lead volume decreased by approximately 30% (from 622 L8W to 486 last week and pacing to 552 this week) across channels</li><li>- Traffic data shows stabilization after initial drops, suggesting the worst decline might be over</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><ul><li>- The team is analyzing if recent industry factors (particularly China-related industries) are affecting lead volume</li></ul><div>- Recent content emails have been generating deals, showing this channel still works despite variability</div><ul><li>- Economic uncertainty and tariff news (April 2nd) are significantly impacting prospect behavior and decision-making</li><li>- The conversion API improvements in Meta are delivering better signals to the algorithm</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>- Restructure the Top of Funnel meeting, including marketing team members to discuss past/upcoming webinars and emails specifically (reviewing copy, topic, etc)</li></ul><div>- Team to explore using HubSpot data (page visits, etc.) for lead scoring</div><ul><li>- Rafael to investigate optimizing post-webinar engagement sequences</li></ul><div><br></div>','WeeklySummary',17,'2025-04-10 19:13:20.000998','2025-04-10 19:13:20.000998');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(115,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>- Current Salesforce field mapping has inconsistencies between objects (leads, contacts, accounts)</li><li>- Five key flows were identified that need improvement to maintain data consistency</li><li>- UTM fields are not being consistently mapped during lead conversion process</li><li>- Some flows are duplicated with different timing settings (1-minute vs. 10-minute delays)</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><ul><li>- Data inconsistency is affecting reporting accuracy and campaign attribution</li><li>- Teams are receiving more accurate information in HubSpot that isn''t being properly transferred to Salesforce</li><li>- The test work Victoria conducted confirmed issues with field mapping during conversion processes</li><li>- Victoria estimated implementation and testing would take about 2 weeks</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>- Victoria to implement lead conversion process field mapping this week as the first priority</li><li>- Victoria to test updates with Bruna who can assist with VPN testing</li><li>- Victoria to provide an update to Tracy before her two-week break</li><li>- Team to follow the five-step implementation plan in the agreed priority order</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',18,'2025-04-10 19:13:20.007428','2025-04-10 19:13:20.007428');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(116,'description',replace('<div class="trix-content">\n  Everything related to lead routing and adding them to specific sequences, from organic, marketing campaigns or paid acquisition channels, whether it''s direct DCs or setter calendars or new business or partners, everything that involves routing and sequencing the right leads to the right AEs or BDRs.\n</div>','\n',char(10)),'Project',98,'2025-04-14 09:10:57.455093','2025-05-20 17:53:53.976262');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(117,'description',replace('<div class="trix-content">\n  <div class="trix-content">\n  everything that is related to talking points for a specific meeting, such as:\n\n• meeting agenda\n• items prepped in advance\n• data points\n• reports\n• specific campaigns\n</div>\n</div>','\n',char(10)),'Project',99,'2025-04-15 21:49:01.580209','2025-05-20 17:54:04.705658');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(118,'content','','WeeklySummary',19,'2025-04-17 18:25:37.490955','2025-04-17 18:25:37.490955');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(119,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Significant recovery in intro volume with 29 intros this week, potentially reaching low 40s compared to previous weeks'' underperformance (12 intros on Wednesday alone vs. L8W average of 3)</li><li>Three specific ad IDs (6697660358233, 6677078398833, 6698071919033) identified as driving the majority of successful introductions</li><li>Despite 11% higher budget spend, previous weeks saw 23% fewer intros and 29% fewer DCs, indicating an improving trend this week</li><li>No-show rate from paid ads stands at 25%, with specific targeting issues being addressed</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><ul><li>"Search everywhere optimization" creative emerging as the highest-performing concept, with budget being shifted to support these ads</li><li>Improved performance after implementing offline conversion tracking using customer data since beginning of year</li><li>New lookalike audience for search everywhere optimization showing early positive results</li><li>Team identified that some ad creatives were generating leads but not converting to intros or DCs</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>Salo meeting with vendor to optimize campaign performance and report findings back to Sarah</li><li>Team developing new creative formats including quiz-style approach and content emphasizing pain points</li><li>Budget increase to be completed, with goal of 43-55 intros in week three of April</li><li>Continue refining targeting to address quality concerns while maintaining growing lead volume</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',20,'2025-04-17 18:25:37.598320','2025-04-17 18:55:10.060136');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(120,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>DC to pitch conversion dropped to 45% in April compared to 75-77% in February/March - lowest since December 2023</li><li>Forecast reduced to $100K for April based on current pipeline and conversion challenges</li><li>Only 4 of 14 closed deals this month had pitches held in April, showing high reliance on aging opportunities</li><li>Contract-to-deal conversion remains healthy at 52%, indicating issues are primarily in middle funnel</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Quality issues driving low DC-to-pitch conversion: prospects seeking services outside our offerings, unclear about meeting purpose, or expressing economic concerns</li><li>Several top performers (Mark Elkington, Sadie, David) showing minimal sales this month while historically weaker reps are closing deals</li><li>Sales team not effectively articulating value proposition and connecting solutions to client pain points</li><li>New product packages communicated in Conclave meetings not effectively reaching sales team</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>Lindsay implementing new contract qualification criteria: 1) confirmed signer/decision maker, 2) clear established next steps, 3) finalized pricing</li><li>Nick developing standardized DC and pitch evaluation process with consistent feedback mechanisms</li><li>Team focusing on improving storytelling and value-based selling approach to better address client pain points</li><li>Nick to analyze DCs by rep to determine specific patterns and causes of conversion challenges</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',21,'2025-04-17 18:25:37.974597','2025-04-17 18:55:10.075953');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(121,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>"How to get mentioned in AI search results" webinar generated 15 DCs so far against a target of 20 (66% before webinar, 34% typically come after)</li><li>White label partner webinar has collected approximately 200 qualified leads prior to launch</li><li>Monday standalone email to targeted budget segment generated 8 DCs, performing better than typical campaigns</li><li>Email performance stable but not growing - blog/monthly consulting emails generating consistent but moderate results</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><ul><li>SEO-focused content consistently outperforms other topics in engagement and conversion</li><li>Email copy lacks urgency and specific data points, particularly in calls-to-action</li><li>Under-budget lead re-qualification campaign successfully converted at least one deal last month</li><li>Webinar format for white label partners requiring different qualification approach than standard leads</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>David creating pre-webinar survey questions to qualify white label partner leads before the event</li><li>Team revising Monday email copy to include more specific data, stronger pain emphasis, and clearer calls-to-action</li><li>BDRs to qualify white label leads before scheduling qualified ones with David</li><li>Future emails to focus more on SEO topics which have shown better engagement than other subjects</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',22,'2025-04-17 18:25:38.053267','2025-04-17 18:55:10.094001');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(122,'content','<ul><li>Salo and Barbara preparing testing version for Colin and Nick to review</li><li>If approved, chatbot will be running this week</li><li>Salo will inform Victor and the sales team when the chatbot goes live</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',23,'2025-04-17 18:25:38.124302','2025-04-17 18:25:38.124302');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(123,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Transition to Looker dashboard planned for TOF weekly meetings for better visualization</li><li>Current boofunnel reports require significant manual updates causing data reliability issues</li><li>Several formula issues identified in reporting dashboards affecting accuracy</li><li>Data comparison between form-submitted and lead enrichment information showing inconsistencies</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Current reporting structure breaks when new metrics are added or data structure changes</li><li>Week-over-week and quarter views in reports rarely used but complicate maintenance</li><li>Traffic data discrepancies between current platform and SEMrush creating validation challenges</li><li>Automated reporting breaking when new metrics are added to summary tabs</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>Evaluate switching lead enrichment system to pull traffic info from SEMrush for more accuracy</li><li>Bruna to fix broken funnel view for DCs and update pitch health tracking in reports</li><li>Simplify boofunnel report by removing week-over-week and quarter views to improve maintainability</li><li>Implement DC-to-pitch conversion metrics in summary tab to better track this critical metric</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',24,'2025-04-17 18:25:38.139678','2025-04-17 18:55:10.104993');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(124,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Partner webinar leads reaching ~200 prospects with registration continuing to grow</li><li>Leads remaining in Outreach sequences too long when not engaging, creating list hygiene issues</li><li>Meeting type settings preventing some prospects from receiving marketing nurture emails</li><li>Current lead removal process inefficient when contacts are made outside of Outreach</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Prospects who scheduled meetings months ago not being properly nurtured due to meeting type settings</li><li>White label partner leads require different qualification approach than standard leads</li><li>Manual removal process needed when leads are contacted outside the Outreach system</li><li>BDRs need specialized training to properly qualify partner opportunities</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>Bruna to change Outreach sequence to remove Sam''s booking link and route partner webinar leads to BDRs</li><li>David to create supporting documents for BDRs about the white label partnership program</li><li>Implement process for regular removal of stagnant leads from sequences (potentially every 2 months)</li><li>Establish clearer process for manually removing leads from sequences when contacted outside Outreach</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',25,'2025-04-17 18:25:38.158468','2025-04-17 18:55:10.113464');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(125,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Joe''s analysis segmented clients by industry and risk profiles to assess potential impact of economic uncertainty</li><li>Analysis showed potential $95K impact if all clients reduced spending by 10% (though unlikely scenario)</li><li>New business acquisition identified as more vulnerable than existing client retention during market shifts</li><li>Existing clients who have seen performance proving more resilient to economic concerns</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Clear distinction identified between new business and existing client behavior during uncertainty</li><li>Market volatility in early April likely temporarily froze decision-making for prospects</li><li>Many current clients signing year-long renewals, showing continued confidence</li><li>Small business owners (not matching ideal client profile) most affected by economic news</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>Continue monitoring client performance across different risk segments</li><li>Maintain awareness of economic indicators that might affect client acquisition and retention</li><li>Develop strategies to address increased sales resistance due to economic uncertainty</li><li>Refine understanding of which prospects are most affected by market conditions</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',26,'2025-04-17 18:46:44.750791','2025-04-17 18:55:10.086195');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(126,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Handover challenges identified as part of broader communication problems rather than isolated issues</li><li>Insufficient information collection during discovery and pitch phases affecting account manager preparation</li><li>Joe shared example from Halo meeting showing effective strategy communication and value demonstration</li><li>Sales not discovering enough about clients'' pain points to properly brief account managers</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Value-based selling approach missing, making handovers difficult due to lack of meaningful information</li><li>Current technical/feature-focused selling doesn''t uncover client pain points effectively</li><li>Account management team working to improve storytelling and demonstrating value to clients</li><li>Handover problems stem from gap in sales approach rather than process breakdown</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>Develop more structured handover approach focusing on client pain points and prescribed solutions</li><li>Improve discovery and pitch process to collect better information that can be transferred</li><li>Need to shift from feature-based selling to value-based problem-solving approach</li><li>Re-evaluate training for both sales and account management to ensure consistent messaging</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',27,'2025-04-17 18:55:10.120416','2025-04-17 18:55:10.120416');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(127,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Field mapping project focused on ensuring proper data transfer during lead conversion process</li><li>Team identified key fields for mapping between leads, accounts, contacts, and opportunities</li><li>Victoria waiting for field mapping completion before developing associated workflow</li><li>Project critical for ensuring data consistency and tracking through sales process</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Team decided to focus on essential tracking fields rather than including all possible fields</li><li>UTM fields recently created for contacts needed validation for proper mapping</li><li>Current field mapping doesn''t capture all necessary information during conversion</li><li>Project addresses foundation for accurate reporting and attribution</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>Bruna to test field mapping by end of next morning to pass to Victoria</li><li>Focus on mapping essential tracking fields including UTMs and qualification data</li><li>Validate whether UTM fields were recently created for contacts for proper mapping</li><li>Ensure account and opportunity fields are updated properly from contact information</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',28,'2025-04-17 18:55:10.124309','2025-04-17 18:55:10.124309');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(128,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>HR sourcing more candidates but many proving unqualified during interviews</li><li>Team has raised standards for hiring based on current successful reps</li><li>Recent interviews resulting in many rejections due to higher quality bar</li><li>Interview process taking up significant time on Nick''s calendar</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Previous experience shows training cannot overcome fundamental skill/aptitude gaps</li><li>Nick, Lindsay, and Santos aligned on maintaining higher standards despite hiring needs</li><li>Lack of consistent hiring pipeline identified as an ongoing challenge</li><li>Current team composition showing gaps with several underperforming legacy reps</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>Nick reviewing list of candidates to potentially expedite screening process</li><li>Continue maintaining higher standards despite pressure to fill positions</li><li>Establish consistent pipeline of sales candidates similar to sales lead management</li><li>HR needs to source candidates that better match the raised standards</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',29,'2025-04-17 18:55:10.129192','2025-04-17 18:55:10.129192');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(129,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Overall lead volume down to below 500 (target is 600+) with quiz leads most significantly affected (dropped from 350+ to 214-236)</li><li>DC quality issues resulting in low conversion to pitches (lowest DC-to-pitch conversion since December 2023)</li><li>Organic lead volume showing signs of stabilization but still below historical averages</li><li>Several prospects appearing confused about discovery call purpose or seeking services outside our offerings</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Multiple factors contributing to lower quality: economic concerns, service mismatches, and qualification issues</li><li>Quality issues appearing across channels, not isolated to a single source or campaign</li><li>Having multiple team members on calls seems to help build trust but may undermine individual rep credibility</li><li>Approach effectiveness varies depending on sales rep strength (better for stronger reps like Mark, Drew, Jacob)</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>Nick developing more standardized DC outline/evaluation process to improve conversion rates</li><li>Team to monitor recent stabilization in lead volume to ensure recovery continues</li><li>Victor, Salo and marketing team to have dedicated Wednesday meetings focusing on webinars, emails, and lead quality</li><li>Team evaluating whether having multiple people on calls is sustainable versus building individual rep capabilities</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',30,'2025-04-17 18:56:50.854942','2025-04-17 18:58:57.694745');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(130,'content','<div><strong>organic &amp; mkt campaigns channels</strong></div><ul><li>lower TOF volume (leads and dc''s) on organic channel (mkt campaigns is actually pacing pretty in line with L3M avg for dc''s)</li><li>however, pretty low dc to pitch conversion on both channels (organic at 38% X 51% L3M and mkt campaigns at 40% X 49% L3M) causing an even lower number of pitches&nbsp;</li></ul><div>&nbsp;<br><strong>paid acquisition</strong></div><ul><li>low performance on the 1st half of the month. last week was great and it did get us a lot of intros, which are converting to dc''s and pitches (overall dc to pitch conversion increased a bit specially due to this channel)</li><li>we weren''t seeing the same performance this week until yesterday EOD, but then we finished thursday with 12 intros (total of 30 this week so far) and 11 DCs. possibly keeping same momentum (or even surpassing) of last week. so far spent 6.2k X 8.4k from last week</li><li>we might get a couple of deals still this month (both tree jaws and stoops nyc are in proposal out, but only stopps is forecasted for this month)</li></ul><div><br></div>','WeeklySummary',31,'2025-04-24 19:51:59.815560','2025-04-25 09:31:51.337490');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(131,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Team exploring HubSpot''s AI-powered lead scoring system to better identify high-value prospects</li><li>Need to leverage behavioral data (page visits, engagement) in addition to firmographic data</li></ul><div>Tracking high-intent page visits (consulting, work with us, contact) can provide valuable intent signals</div><ul><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><ul><li>HubSpot offers native AI-powered scoring features (engagement score and fit score) that aren''t currently utilized</li><li>Current lead scoring is primarily based on firmographic data and doesn''t fully leverage intent signals</li><li>Team needs to better understand how to map HubSpot stages with Salesforce opportunity stages</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>Bruna to explore and activate HubSpot''s AI-powered scoring features</li><li>Team to review what data points should be included in the scoring model</li><li>Bruna to investigate and explain how the scoring systems work to the team</li><li>Incorporate findings from ad creative analysis to better target ideal client segments</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',32,'2025-04-24 19:51:59.822002','2025-04-24 19:51:59.822002');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(132,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>47 intros generated last week (highest in 8 weeks) compared to 8-week average of 31</li><li>17 DCs scheduled last week and 6 DCs scheduled so far this week</li><li>Conversion rate from intro to DC at 58% vs. 54% 8-week average</li><li>Two opportunities currently in proposal stage from paid acquisition</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Increased ad spend contributed to last week''s strong performance</li><li>Top-performing ads focus on "Search Everywhere Optimization" and target B2B companies/home services</li><li>Team reviewing 14 new creative scripts with various approaches including problem-solution frameworks, decision cost, expertise establishment, and conceptual methodologies</li><li>New ad creative for discovery calls needs careful messaging to set appropriate expectations</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>David to provide Cody with guidance on talk tracks for BDRs handling leads from the new ad creative</li><li>Team to complete review of 14 new ad scripts, with David, Lindsay, and Cody providing feedback</li><li>New creatives scheduled for recording next week with expected launch in the second week of May</li><li>Monitor this week''s performance which currently shows a slower pace compared to last week</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',33,'2025-04-24 19:51:59.828193','2025-04-24 19:51:59.828193');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(133,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Currently at 69k in MRR with 29k in contract, having a clear path to reach 85k according to sales leadership</li><li>Pitch show rates have dropped from 75% in previous months to 65% in April</li><li>Pitch to contract, contract to deal, and AOV metrics are all up compared to the last three months</li><li>Limited number of opportunities in the "proposal out" stage is a concern for hitting targets</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Team implementing new contract rules requiring reps to confirm: clear next steps, identified signer/decision maker, and prospect agreement on pricing before sending contracts</li><li>Paid channel leads often close quickly as they tend to be bottom-of-funnel with previous agency experience</li><li>Need to analyze call recordings more systematically to identify patterns in prospect objections</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>Nick to quantify the increase in rescheduled and missed pitches to better understand the pattern</li><li>Team to explore implementing scoring systems for intro calls and DCs to improve qualification process</li><li>Cody to ensure the team is using the correct Chili Piper extension and sent instructions to uninstall the old one</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',34,'2025-04-24 19:51:59.831539','2025-04-24 19:51:59.831539');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(134,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>DC to pitch conversion rate is significantly below historical performance despite team improvements</li><li>Team is initiating a test targeting 52 under $750 budget leads that meet specific qualification criteria (high urgency + 500+ in monthly organic traffic for local businesses and 1000+ for national)</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Leads showing high urgency and substantial organic traffic (500+ for local, 1000+ for national) may indicate untapped potential despite lower budgets</li><li>Historical challenges with under $750 budget leads include high maintenance, low close rates, and pricing complaints</li><li>Team is developing a scoring system for intro calls to better qualify prospects, with Nick and Cody already working on concepts</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>Cody to create email copy for a new under $750 lead sequence by early next week</li><li>Team will implement a 30-day test focused on highly qualified under $750 leads (about 10 per BDR)</li><li>Nick and Victor reviewing recorded calls to verify market conditions hypothesis and identify patterns</li><li>Team to discuss scoring implementation in the next TOF meeting with inputs from Cody''s preliminary work</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',35,'2025-04-24 19:51:59.834836','2025-04-24 19:51:59.834836');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(135,'content','<div><strong>Key Performance Insights</strong></div><ul><li>Latest promotional email ("Content Creation Hacks") generated 4 DCs, slightly above the average of 3</li><li>Previous webinar "How to get mentioned in Google''s AI search results" generated 16 DCs</li><li>Current webinar (Meta and Google Hacks) showing poor registration with only 1 DC so far</li><li>Partner webinar from this week had 4 DCs + David is manually reaching out to higher potential leads that responded a fup survey (potentially do that for other webinars as well?)</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Critical Observations &amp; Strategic Insights</strong></div><div>Testing inviting closed-lost opps that moved to pitch prep in Q4/2024 and had paid products for webinar registration. Could reopen conversations with qualified prospects</div><ul><li>Ad creative categories reveal effective frameworks: problem-solution, decision cost, expertise establishment, conceptual methodologies, and small business pain points</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Tactical Focus &amp; Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>Implement test campaign targeting Q4 2024 closed-lost opportunities with PPC/Level Up products to boost webinar registration</li><li>David to create email copy by end of day, with outreach to be sent by Friday</li><li>Marketing team to revise the subject line for the Monday promotional email based on feedback</li><li>Bruna to monitor and redirect any partner webinar bookings to David rather than BDRs</li></ul>','WeeklySummary',36,'2025-04-24 19:51:59.837831','2025-04-24 19:51:59.837831');
INSERT INTO action_text_rich_texts VALUES(140,'description',replace('<div class="trix-content">\n  <div class="trix-content">\n  \n</div>\n</div>','\n',char(10)),'Project',104,'2025-05-20 17:26:14.090311','2025-05-20 17:31:04.431866');
