INSERT INTO comments VALUES(130,'<div><strong>Paid Deals<br></strong><br></div><ul><li>Brief summary: There are indications that paid deal is becoming more prevalent as clients are opting for paid marketing solutions.</li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li>Main questions/blockers/concerns:&nbsp;<ul><li>Lower Average Order Value (AOV) as many clients are choosing paid-only or Level Up deals ($2,796 blended AOV, potentially as low as $2,300 without a large deal)</li><li>Half of closed deals are paid-only, with most being Level Up deals</li></ul></li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li>Additional Information:&nbsp;<ul><li>Clients are expressing preference for paid marketing over SEO due to budget constraints and desire for quantifiable short-term returns</li><li>The team is seeing clients who specifically want paid marketing and not SEO, contrary to their previous reputation as primarily a content/SEO agency</li></ul></li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information not related to specific projects<br></strong><br></div><ul><li>Potential economic impact on sales:&nbsp;<ul><li>Political climate and economic anxiety affecting SMB purchasing decisions and commitment levels</li><li>Clients have tighter budgets and are seeking more quantifiable returns on investment</li><li>Lower client willingness to commit to longer-term contracts</li></ul></li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li>Revenue recognition concerns:&nbsp;<ul><li>Discussion about how Level Up deal revenue is recognized for the sales team vs. actual billing</li><li>Sales team gets credited for $1,000 on Level Up deals even when the company might bill $2,400+ based on actual ad spend</li><li>This accounting method may be artificially depressing the reported sales team performance</li></ul></li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li>Current sales performance:&nbsp;<ul><li>23 deals closed worth approximately $64,000 MRR as of meeting date</li><li>Comparing to March 2024: similar number of deals (20 vs. 19) at the same point in the month, but significantly lower MRR ($55,379 vs. $72,000)</li><li>Current month''s performance heavily dependent on a potential $14k deal that was almost rejected</li><li>Team is performing with fewer reps than last year (9-10 vs. 11-12)</li></ul></li></ul>',68,3,'2025-03-24 16:48:37.840246','2025-03-31 14:21:26.546636','2025-03-20',5);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(131,'<div><strong>Sales Process Improvement on Bottom of Funnel</strong></div><ul><li>Brief summary: Discussion around contract conversion rates and sales rep behaviors when sending agreements.</li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li>Main questions/blockers/concerns:&nbsp;<ul><li>Contract-to-deal conversion rate is lower than historical averages (currently at 55%, compared to 64% in 2024 and 55% in 2023)</li><li>Some sales reps (specifically Mark and Spencer) have lower conversion rates (around 33%)</li><li>Inconsistent practices around when to send contracts</li></ul></li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li>Next steps and who is responsible:&nbsp;<ul><li>Nick will present findings on which reps are contributing to lower conversion rates at the Monday meeting</li><li>Continue pilot of sales rules with Chaplin to improve contract discipline</li></ul></li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li>Additional Information:&nbsp;<ul><li>There''s a tension between individual rep performance (MRR) versus disciplined contract sending</li><li>Historical contract-to-deal conversion rates appear to fluctuate between 55-65%</li><li>Team is comparing current metrics to previous months, which may not account for seasonality and team changes</li></ul></li></ul>',87,3,'2025-03-24 16:49:14.907226','2025-03-24 16:50:45.340941','2025-03-20',5);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(132,'<div><strong>Brief Summary</strong></div><div>The team discussed recent changes to paid ad copy, removing AI-focused messaging and replacing it with more industry-specific content. This change was implemented around the end of February. The team is noticing that the volume of intros coming from paid ads is currently lower than expected but the quality of leads that reach the sales team is higher.<br><br></div><div><strong>Main Questions/Blockers/Concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Current intro volume from paid ads is lower than expected despite increased spending</li><li>Need to evaluate if the change in ad copy (removing AI focus) is having a negative impact on lead volume</li><li>Need for feedback from BDRs on the new ad creative/copy</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>Cody to collect BDR feedback on the new ad creative and relay to Sarah/Neil (Cody''s responsibility)</li><li>Team to monitor intro volume closely in the coming weeks as paid ads spend increases (Victor''s responsibility)</li><li>BDR team to provide qualitative feedback on leads coming through the new ad creative (Cody''s team responsibility)</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Nick mentioned there are three deals on the board in March from marketing campaigns, with two from general campaigns and one from travel and hospitality</li><li>Neil and Mike reached out to Nick expressing concerns about lead volume</li><li>Higher quality leads are now reaching the sales team after being filtered through the BDR team</li></ul>',82,3,'2025-03-24 16:52:08.441076','2025-03-24 16:52:08.441076','2025-03-18',2);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(133,'<div><strong>Brief Summary</strong></div><div>Briefly mentioned as context for the web form changes and new fields being collected (monthly organic traffic + business terrirtory). The team is now collecting additional data in Salesforce that will be visible to BDRs but not yet used for segmentation.<br><br></div><div><strong>Main Questions/Blockers/Concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Need to ensure BDRs can see the new form fields in their tools</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next Steps</strong></div><ul><li>Bruna to add the new form fields to outreach so BDRs can see them (Bruna''s responsibility)</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Two new fields are being added to forms as discussed in prior meetings</li><li>The fields "business territory" and others are now being collected but not yet used for lead routing or qualification</li></ul>',68,3,'2025-03-24 16:53:47.491244','2025-03-24 16:53:47.491244','2025-03-18',2);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(135,'<div><strong>Brief Summary</strong></div><ul><li>The meeting focused field mapping/cleanup across different Salesforce objects. They planned field creation for Events, Campaign Members, and Opportunities to ensure consistent data mapping.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main Questions/Problems/Blockers</strong></div><ul><li>Redundant fields across objects causing confusion and inconsistency</li><li>Missing data fields in Events and Campaign Members preventing proper reporting</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next Steps and Responsibilities</strong></div><ul><li>Victor: Document which fields need to be mapped between which objects</li><li>Victoria: Create the required fields in Account, Event, and Campaign Member objects (within 2-3 days)</li><li>Both: Schedule a follow-up meeting to implement automation for transferring information between objects</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Victoria confirmed there''s an existing flow from Lead/Contact to Campaign Member that might need adjustment</li><li>Some fields they previously used (Business Type, Industry) were removed from forms and replaced with Monthly Organic Traffic and Business Territory</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information Not Related to Main Projects</strong></div><ul><li>They intend to start a field cleanup initiative, particularly for the Opportunity object, as Victoria mentioned having many initiatives stalled due to lack of available fields</li></ul>',90,3,'2025-03-24 16:57:48.052979','2025-03-24 16:57:48.052979','2025-03-21',3);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(136,'<div><strong>Brief summary:</strong></div><div>The team discussed collecting additional qualification data through web forms, including monthly organic traffic and business territory fields. They''re testing whether traffic volume could be a better qualifying indicator than marketing spend alone.<br><br></div><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns:</strong></div><ul><li>13% of leads currently classified as "unqualified" (below $1500 monthly spend) have traffic above 500, suggesting they might actually be qualified for direct discovery calls</li><li>Need to gather more data to validate this new qualification approach<br><br></li></ul><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible:</strong></div><ul><li>Continue collecting and analyzing data from the new form fields (Bruno implied as responsible)</li><li>Assess how these newly identified leads perform through the funnel<br><br></li></ul><div><strong>Additional Information:</strong></div><ul><li>They removed Industry and Business Type fields but kept the total number of fields the same</li><li>Early data shows promise but needs more validation</li></ul>',88,3,'2025-03-24 19:21:21.013778','2025-03-28 18:06:23.376171','2025-03-24',1);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(137,'<div><strong>Brief summary:</strong></div><ul><li>The team is experiencing challenges with their Meta (Facebook) paid acquisition channel. Issues include ads being flagged, tracking problems, and campaigns entering learning phases repeatedly, affecting lead volume and performance.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns:</strong></div><ul><li>Tracking pixel issues disrupted campaign performance for about four days</li><li>Meta ads went into learning phase due to creative changes</li><li>Erratic performance is making it difficult to rely on this channel for consistent lead flow</li><li>Potential pipeline shortage for April due to lower intro call volume</li><li>Budget allocation and spend pacing concerns<br><br></li></ul><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible:</strong></div><ul><li>Complete pixel fix (Solo indicated this would be done today)</li><li>Continue spending the remaining month''s budget ($6K over 7 days)</li><li>Monitor for potential spike in intro calls if campaigns exit learning phase (Cody''s team to handle)<br><br></li></ul><div><strong>Additional Information:</strong></div><ul><li>Total monthly budget is $20K with $14K already spent</li><li>Previous daily spend was averaging $650-850</li><li>Despite issues, they had 25 scheduled calls and 20 discovery calls from paid channels last week</li><li>Cody''s team is fully staffed and ready to handle potential volume increase</li></ul>',82,3,'2025-03-24 19:22:00.289868','2025-03-24 19:22:00.289868','2025-03-24',1);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(138,'<div><strong>Brief summary:</strong></div><ul><li>The team is experiencing challenges with bottom-of-funnel metrics, particularly with marketing campaign conversion rates. Webinars and consulting emails are underperforming compared to previous months.<br><br></li></ul><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns:</strong></div><ul><li>Webinar and consulting email channels not converting well this month</li><li>Issue appears to be between pitch preparation and contract stages</li><li>Some representatives are sending out contracts too liberally, significantly impacting conversion metrics<br><br></li></ul><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible:</strong></div><ul><li>Upcoming training for the sales team tomorrow to address contract sending practices (implied Sales leadership)</li><li>Marion to adjust marketing copy to focus on combined services rather than single services to potentially improve AOV</li><li>Sales to provide more detailed feedback to marketing team on lead quality issues<br><br></li></ul><div><strong>Additional Information:</strong></div><ul><li>Recent "Future of Organic Traffic" webinar performed well with 23 discovery calls and 9 pitch preps</li><li>Recent AI-focused email about new Google features generated 12 discovery calls</li><li>Feedback that some leads are startups wanting strategic rather than executional support<br><br></li></ul>',87,3,'2025-03-24 19:24:03.988144','2025-03-24 19:24:03.988144','2025-03-24',1);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(139,'<div><strong>Brief summary:</strong></div><ul><li>The team briefly discussed negative Reddit reviews affecting sales, with at least one known lost deal due to prospects finding these reviews.<br><br></li></ul><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns:</strong></div><ul><li>Multiple negative Reddit posts visible in search results are hurting sales</li><li>Difficult to keep removing negative content as new posts continue to appear<br><br></li></ul><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible:</strong></div><ul><li>Solo and team exploring hiring a Reddit expert to address the issue properly</li><li>Plans to add review links to meeting reminders in ChiliPiper (Bruno)</li><li>Adding review highlights to pitch decks discussed</li><li>Planning to discuss specific solutions at the "top funnel" meeting tomorrow<br><br></li></ul><div><strong>Additional Information:</strong></div><ul><li>Team has managed to remove one particularly concerning Reddit post</li><li>Company has created dedicated review pages that rank well (NP Juice 2 reviews, New Patel reviews)</li><li>Also working on improving TrustPilot reviews quarterly<br><br></li></ul>',87,3,'2025-03-24 19:25:08.514090','2025-03-24 19:25:08.514090','2025-03-24',1);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(141,'<div><strong>Additional Information (potential new projects)</strong></div><ul><li>Exploration of implementing a chatbot on the website based on success in Brazil&nbsp;<ul><li>Brazil implementation has resulted in 7 deals in 2024 and 800K in TCB</li><li>Uses HubSpot chat features with decision-tree qualification flow</li><li>Before implementing in North America, need to consult with Colin and Gullikson</li><li>US website has approximately 10x more traffic than Brazil site</li><li>The team seems interested in testing this approach</li></ul></li></ul>',88,3,'2025-03-24 19:25:40.001506','2025-03-24 19:25:40.001506','2025-03-24',1);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(142,'<div><strong>Brief summary</strong></div><ul><li>The team discussed performance of Meta paid acquisition, including current costs per intro call, conversion rates, budget spending, and targeting parameters. There''s concern about the increased costs compared to previous benchmarks.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main problems/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Cost per intro call has increased from $121 to $146</li><li>The team is debating whether to open targeting to lower budget prospects ($750-$1500) for more volume</li><li>Ad creative feedback loop needs improvement to optimize performance</li><li>The team has spent $2,200 so far this week with 14 intro calls and 2 discovery calls</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and responsibilities</strong></div><ul><li>Saulo: Meeting with the vendor managing the ads to address increased costs</li><li>Saulo: Create a slide with review links by end of the week to add to the pitch deck</li><li>Cody: Get BDRs to provide specific feedback on ad creatives and emails</li><li>Cody: Train BDRs to ask clarifying questions when prospects mention ads/emails</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Weekly budget target is $6,000</li><li>Expected outcome: 35-40 intro calls this week</li><li>Decision to maintain current targeting (above $1,500 budget only)</li><li>Previous AI-focused ads were outliers with higher volume, but lower quality leads</li></ul>',82,3,'2025-03-25 19:24:13.843397','2025-03-25 19:30:21.841888','2025-03-25',2);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(143,'<div><strong>Brief summary</strong></div><ul><li>Discussion focused on improving the feedback loop between BDRs, sales reps, and the marketing team to optimize ad performance and lead quality.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main problems/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>BDRs are not gathering specific enough feedback about creatives from prospects</li><li>Need for more structured approach to collecting and sharing prospect feedback</li><li>Uncertainty about whether BDRs are working the organic leads sequence properly</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and responsibilities</strong></div><ul><li>Cody: Create training for BDRs on how to pivot conversations to gather feedback</li><li>Cody: Provide clear examples of feedback Saulo needs about creatives</li><li>Cody: Check if BDRs are working the organic leads sequence properly</li><li>Saulo: Share webinar content calendar with Cody</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Saulo needs feedback specifically on creative elements, emails, and webinar titles</li><li>Team discussed creating a structured approach to collecting feedback with specific questions</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information (not related to existing projects)</strong></div><ul><li>Discussion about removing notifications for leads under $750 budget in the "Let''s grow your traffic" channel</li><li>Team created a slide with review links that will be included in pitch call invites</li><li>The quiz pop-up has already been removed from a page</li></ul><div><br></div>',88,3,'2025-03-25 19:27:23.472299','2025-03-25 19:31:50.370053','2025-03-25',2);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(144,'<div><strong>Brief summary</strong></div><ul><li>Brief discussion about analyzing closed-lost opportunities and improving pipeline management.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main problems/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Potential issues with pipeline management accuracy</li><li>Opportunities moving to pitch prep or contract stage prematurely</li><li>Need for better understanding of why opportunities are lost -&gt; IMPORTANT</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and responsibilities</strong></div><ul><li>Lyndsay: Running Salesforce pipeline opportunity management calls with reps weekly</li><li>Team: Table the closed-lost analysis for now and revisit in July</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Lyndsay mentioned starting pipeline management calls similar to what was done at previous agency</li><li><em>Current close-loss reasons in the system are not specific enough to draw conclusions -&gt; IMPORTANT</em></li></ul>',87,3,'2025-03-25 19:29:01.108094','2025-04-10 16:39:41.667913','2025-03-25',2);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(148,'<div><strong>Brief summary:</strong></div><ul><li>The meeting focused on reviewing the profitability analysis of the Meta paid advertising channel. Victor presented data showing that the ads are profitable, with approximately 10% profit based on billed TCV. The team discussed metrics like cost per pitch, pitch-to-deal conversion rates, and monthly breakdowns of profitability.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns:</strong></div><ul><li>There''s tension between mg and mk regarding how to calculate ROI - mk believes calculations should be based on in-month revenue vs. spend, while mg may have a different view (cohort basis)</li><li>Whether the "other marketing costs" assumption is fair in the calculations</li><li>How to improve profitability beyond the current ~10% level</li><li>Finding the right benchmark for cost per pitch that correlates with pitch-to-deal conversion rates</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible:</strong></div><ul><li>Sarah will message mg to set up a meeting for Thursday or Friday to review the calculations before Tuesday''s larger meeting</li><li>Victor and Saulo will present the analysis at the Tuesday meeting, emphasizing that ads are profitable</li><li>The team needs to confirm with mg whether the calculation approach makes sense for him</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information:</strong></div><ul><li>The data shows that Meta ads are profitable even with a cost per pitch as high as $1,000 in March</li><li>February appeared to be a particularly good month with profits above 20% and cost per pitch around $500</li><li>The leads from Meta ads seem to have higher GP margins than other clients - "it''s cheaper to deliver the services to these clients"</li><li>There''s a potential "compounding effect" where ads become more profitable over time as they build on themselves</li></ul>',82,3,'2025-03-27 13:29:53.753322','2025-03-27 13:29:53.753322','2025-03-26',3);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(149,'<div>-&gt; <strong>Is this the typical way pipeline meetings are run?<br></strong><br></div><ul><li>Yes, the general approach of reviewing opportunities by stage (commit, contract sent, proposal out) is typical. However, most effective pipeline meetings include:</li><li>A clear agenda sent beforehand</li><li>Consistent qualification criteria across the team</li><li>More structured discussion format for each opportunity</li><li>Time-bound conversations to maintain pace</li><li>Clear action items documented for follow-up</li></ul><div><br></div><div>-&gt; <strong>How can we improve this process? Standardize opportunity review format</strong> - Create a template each rep must follow when presenting:&nbsp;<br><br></div><ul><li>Opportunity name/size</li><li>Current stage</li><li>Last activity/next steps</li><li>Specific blockers</li><li>Clear close timeline with reasoning</li><li>Support needed</li><li>Limit time per opportunity and focus on actionable items (ie. next steps) rather than storytelling</li><li>Add pipeline metrics - Begin meetings with overall metrics:&nbsp;<ul><li>Current pipeline vs. target</li><li>Conversion rates between stages</li><li>Average sales cycle length</li><li>Win/loss trends</li></ul></li></ul><div><br></div><div>-&gt; <strong>Current Criteria Used by Reps to Move Opportunities:<br></strong><br></div><ul><li>For moving to <strong>Contract Sent</strong>:<ul><li>Verbal agreement received ("They agreed, said yes, and sent over a contract")</li><li>Decision maker confirmation ("The person I spoke with is the designated signer")</li><li>Pricing agreement ("Was confused about the pricing when I sent him the contract")</li><li>Positive pitch feedback ("Pitch last week. Contract went out yesterday")</li></ul></li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li>For <strong>Proposal Out</strong> stage:<ul><li>Discovery completed with identified needs</li><li>Client engagement level (responsiveness)</li><li>Technical validation completed (example: "will was able to look at search console")</li><li>Competitive positioning ("They were looking at us in one other group")</li></ul></li></ul><div><br></div><div>-&gt; <strong>Recommended Standardized Framework:<br></strong><br></div><ul><li><strong>When to Move to Pitch Prep:</strong><ul><li>Client has confirmed specific pain points and needs</li><li>Budget parameters are understood (even if rough)</li><li>Decision-making process/stakeholders are identified</li><li>Client has agreed to review a proposal</li></ul></li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li><strong>When to Move to Contract Stage:</strong><ul><li>Client has given verbal approval on the proposal</li><li>Pricing and scope have been confirmed/agreed upon</li><li>Decision maker is directly engaged in the process</li><li>Client has indicated specific timeline for signing</li><li>All technical questions have been addressed</li></ul></li></ul><div><br></div><div>-&gt; <strong>Supporting Rules</strong></div><ul><li>If a client goes dark (no response for 3+ business days), opportunity should be re-evaluated</li><li>No opportunity moves to contract stage without confirmed next steps for signing</li><li>All contracts require clear follow-up cadence (as mentioned: "I always give it a full day... my next move would be Wednesday/Thursday")</li></ul>',87,3,'2025-03-27 14:15:06.175565','2025-03-28 11:05:05.764010','2025-03-25',3);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(168,'<div><strong>Brief Summary</strong></div><ul><li>Discussion on challenges with sales team performance, particularly focusing on how leadership involvement in pitches significantly increases deal closure rates and speeds.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main Questions/Problems/Blockers/Concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Half of the sales team underperforming compared to top performers</li><li>Inconsistent ability to handle objections (e.g., Reddit negative reviews)</li><li>Pipeline management issues with conversion rates from pitch to contract</li><li>Contract sending practices vary widely among reps, resulting individual rep behaviors affecting overall metrics (some reps don''t understand expectations for contract sending)</li><li>Sustainability of current approach where sales leadership joins most pitches</li><li>Need for rep-specific analysis rather than team-level analysis for accurate forecasting</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next Steps and Responsible Persons</strong></div><ul><li>Continue having sales leadership join pitches, prioritizing calls with underperforming reps</li><li>Implement more structured training using successful pitch examples</li><li>Address Mark Chaplin''s specific issue with contract sending metrics</li><li>Continue evaluating individual rep performance to target improvements</li><li>Focus on developing processes that can scale without leadership joining every call</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Team seeing success with "all-out blitz" approach where sales leaders join pitches</li><li>Two types of reps identified: those who can learn/absorb training (Jacob, Mark, Drew) and those who struggle</li><li>Personnel changes may be needed for long-term improvement (Ongoing hiring efforts to address talent gap on sales team)</li><li>Team currently relying heavily on sales leadership to close deals, especially toward month-end</li><li>Reddit negative reviews emerging as a challenge for sales team to overcome</li></ul>',87,2,'2025-03-28 17:48:57.276104','2025-03-28 17:53:29.001713','2025-03-27',5);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(169,'<div><strong>Brief Summary</strong></div><ul><li>Concerns about sustainability of paid acquisition as a reliable lead source, with current month performance relying heavily on opportunities created in previous months.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main Questions/Problems/Blockers/Concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Paid channel not generating expected volume of intros and leads for current month</li><li>Most closed deals from paid came from earlier opportunities, raising concerns about pipeline</li><li>Constant references to "learning phase" causing skepticism</li><li>Potential overreliance on paid acquisition at expense of other channels</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next Steps and Responsible Persons</strong></div><ul><li>Need discussion at Monday meeting and retro about paid channel performance</li><li>Evaluate whether paid acquisition can reliably deliver 5 deals per month going forward</li><li>Balance focus between paid, organic, and marketing campaigns</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Paid acquisition initially positioned as "path to growth" but not meeting expectations</li><li>Concern about marketing focusing too much on paid at expense of organic leads</li><li>Recognition that business remains seasonal with traditional channels still critical</li><li>Conversion rates from paid marketing campaigns actually 15 points higher with BDR involvement</li></ul>',82,2,'2025-03-28 17:50:30.312139','2025-03-28 17:50:30.312139','2025-03-27',5);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(170,'<div><strong>-&gt; TTM Churn</strong><br><br><strong>Brief Summary</strong></div><ul><li>Discussion about refining churn analysis by looking at revenue bands rather than account manager tiers, which provides better insights into client retention patterns.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main Questions/Problems/Blockers/Concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Current reporting mixes account manager titles with revenue buckets, causing confusion</li><li>Team confusion on how to categorize churn when client revenue crosses tiers</li><li>Need to normalize project-based work (like CRO audits) when analyzing churn</li><li>Senior tier accounts showing concerning churn increase in February</li><li>Quality assurance failures leading to significant cancellations</li><li>Content being flagged as AI when it was human-written</li><li>Failure to properly onboard and sell to new decision makers at clients</li><li>Increase in non-payment issues from clients</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next Steps and Responsible Persons</strong></div><ul><li>Adam/Paul: Update reporting to show revenue buckets rather than AM tiers for clarity</li><li>Ryan/Adam: Meet to determine how to normalize project-based work in churn reporting</li><li>Adam: Work on importing level-up churn data to provide cleaner analysis</li><li>Joe/Emily: Implementing new DM (decision maker) process to better handle client transitions</li><li>Emily: Rolling out training on handling new decision makers at clients</li><li>Team: Implementing more client visits, particularly before renewals</li><li>Joe: Encouraging more onsite visits with renewal/upsell potential clients</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Overall positive trend with churn decreasing to 5.2% (trailing 12-month)</li><li>Email marketing churn down 30% year-over-year</li><li>CRO (Conversion Rate Optimization) showing higher churn due to project-based nature</li><li>Senior account managers seeing concerning churn trends with key examples discussed</li><li>True Log ($10k) cancellation due to missed internal backlinks and content issues</li><li>Integrated Engineer lost due to failure to properly engage new decision maker</li><li>Credit insurance update with new provider (Coface) after previous rate increases</li></ul><div><br><strong>-&gt; SEO Team Restructure</strong><br><br></div><div><strong>Main Questions/Problems/Blockers/Concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Mid-tier clients not getting enough direct SME (subject matter expert) support</li><li>Current tier structure not aligned with client needs</li><li>Management structure needs adjustment to support new client-facing model</li><li>Staffing challenges with one mid-tier person recently leaving</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next Steps and Responsible Persons</strong></div><ul><li>Will: Implement restructure within 4-6 weeks (planned completion within 2 months)</li><li>Will: Create SOPs for mid-tier client-facing requirements and AM expectations</li><li>Lindsay (new director): Oversee new structure with dedicated managers for each tier</li><li>Team: Post open for new associate manager position</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Restructuring to allow mid-tier strategists to handle 56% fewer clients</li><li>Lowering senior floor from 8.2k to 7k MRR to better balance workload</li><li>Creating clear separation of duties between associate, mid-tier, and senior strategists</li><li>Promoting from within to fill gaps and improve retention</li><li>Goal is to further reduce churn beyond current stabilization</li></ul>',92,2,'2025-03-28 17:59:28.598131','2025-03-28 17:59:28.598131','2025-03-27',3);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(171,'<div><strong>WEEK OF 03/30 - 04/06 PLANNING</strong></div><div><br></div><ul><li><strong>Brief Summary</strong><ul><li>Meta paid ads have been experiencing technical challenges including tracking pixel issues, ads being flagged, and campaigns repeatedly entering learning phases. Despite these issues, the ads remain profitable (about 10% profit on billed TCV).&nbsp;</li><li>We''ve spent $14K of our $20K monthly budget with $6K remaining for the final days of March.&nbsp;</li><li>Current cost per intro is $146 (up from $121 planned), but the team expects 35-40 intro calls this week.&nbsp;</li><li>There''s concern about April pipeline as most current deals came from opportunities created in previous months rather than new leads.</li></ul></li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li><strong>Next Steps</strong><ul><li>&nbsp;Follow up on pixel fix completion with Saulo</li><li>&nbsp;Review profitability metrics ahead of Monday''s meeting to prepare for discussion about paid channel performance</li><li>&nbsp;Prepare to evaluate whether paid acquisition can reliably deliver 5 deals per month going forward</li><li>&nbsp;Review data from Tuesday''s meeting to understand whether the calculation approach was approved by Mike G</li><li>&nbsp;Work with Cody to ensure team is collecting specific feedback on ad creatives and emails from prospects</li><li>&nbsp;Analyze closed deals from paid to compare GP margins vs other channels</li></ul></li></ul>',82,2,'2025-03-28 18:18:30.799022','2025-03-28 18:18:50.710330','2025-03-28',NULL);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(173,'<div><strong>WEEK OF 03/30 - 04/05 PLANNING</strong><br><br></div><ul><li><strong>Context</strong><ul><li>We''re seeing issues with bottom-of-funnel metrics, particularly in converting from pitch prep to contract stage.&nbsp;</li><li>Sales leadership involvement in pitches has significantly increased deal closure rates.&nbsp;</li><li>Half the sales team is underperforming compared to top performers, with inconsistent handling of objections (especially Reddit reviews).&nbsp;</li><li>Current close-loss reasons in the system aren''t specific enough to draw meaningful conclusions.&nbsp;</li><li>Some reps are sending contracts too liberally, negatively impacting conversion metrics.</li></ul></li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li><strong>Next Steps</strong><ul><li>&nbsp;Review results from last week''s training on contract sending practices</li><li>&nbsp;Check with Marion on adjustments to marketing copy to focus on combined services</li><li>&nbsp;Analyze Mark Chaplin''s specific issue with contract sending metrics</li><li>&nbsp;Follow up on the implementation of Salesforce pipeline opportunity management calls</li><li>&nbsp;Monitor results of sales leadership joining pitches, especially with underperforming reps</li><li>&nbsp;Review update on hiring Reddit expert to address negative reviews</li><li>&nbsp;Check implementation of review links in ChiliPiper meeting reminders</li></ul></li></ul>',87,2,'2025-03-28 18:23:37.513073','2025-03-28 18:23:37.513073','2025-03-28',NULL);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(174,'<ul><li><strong>Brief Summary</strong><ul><li>The team is exploring implementing a chatbot based on success in Brazil (7 deals in 2024, 800K TCV).&nbsp;</li><li>We''re also collecting additional qualification data through web forms, including monthly organic traffic and business territory.&nbsp;</li><li>Early data shows 13% of leads classified as "unqualified" (below $1500 spend) have traffic above 500, suggesting they might be qualified.&nbsp;</li><li>BDRs need to improve their feedback collection on creative elements to help optimize marketing.</li></ul></li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li><strong>Next Steps</strong><ul><li>&nbsp;Check if Saulo has consulted with Colin and Gullikson about chatbot implementation</li><li>&nbsp;Continue analyzing data from the new form fields to validate the traffic-based qualification approach</li><li>&nbsp;Follow up on Cody''s training for BDRs on gathering better creative feedback</li><li>&nbsp;Check if BDRs are properly working the organic leads sequence</li><li>&nbsp;Follow up on whether the review links slide has been included in pitch call invites</li><li>&nbsp;Review discussion about notifications for leads under $750 in the "Let''s grow your traffic" channel</li></ul></li></ul>',88,2,'2025-03-28 18:25:02.216433','2025-03-28 18:25:02.216433','2025-03-28',NULL);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(175,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>Bruna discussed analysis of lost opportunities, noting that many opportunities aren''t progressing past the Discovery Call (DC) stage.</li><li>50% of opportunities lost in March (33 out of 66) were in the "DC Scheduled" stage and didn''t move forward in the funnel.</li><li>Primary reasons for lost opportunities were: no response, low budget, and "old come to b".</li><li>Discussion about lead qualification by BDRs and potential issues with current qualification process.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>How to improve qualification of Discovery Calls since BDRs are now responsible for scheduling these?</li><li>Why is the DC to pitch conversion rate declining? Less DCs resulted in the same number of pitches, suggesting qualification issues.</li><li>How to address that many opportunities are being lost at the early stages of the funnel?</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Bruna will discuss the lost opportunity data with Saulo at the Wednesday meeting.</li><li>Victor and Bruna will continue monitoring the DC to pitch conversion rates for the right moment to address this issue with the team.</li><li>Analysis needed to compare the LES field with the newly implemented field to see how it affects lead qualification.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Bruna created a special analysis of closed lost opportunities showing 76% were lost due to "no response," "low budget," or "old come to b."</li><li>Previous attempts to implement lead qualification standards encountered resistance from the sales leadership (specifically Lindsay)</li></ul>',88,2,'2025-03-31 20:19:07.323544','2025-03-31 20:23:12.414386','2025-03-31',10);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(176,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>March report indicates lower volume of Discovery Calls (DCs) from Meta ads despite higher budget spend.</li><li>Issues with Meta ads campaign in March included: creative changes, budget changes, and pixel problems, which extended "learning phase" and affected campaign performance.</li><li>Conversion is good from DC to intro call despite lower volume.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>Why did Meta ads generate fewer DCs with a higher budget?</li><li>How to stabilize campaign performance and avoid extended learning phases?</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Budget for April has been set, with a week-over-week breakdown.</li><li>Decision made not to change the budget to prevent going into learning phase again.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Out of 6 closed deals in march, 4 were from opportunities created in the previous month and 1 from January, highlighting conversion timeline.</li><li>Current month created 68 opportunities compared to double that number in February.</li><li>Conversion rate needs to be much higher next month to compensate for lower lead volume.</li></ul>',82,2,'2025-03-31 20:21:05.479462','2025-03-31 20:21:05.479462','2025-03-31',10);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(177,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>Discussion about field mappings created by Victoria for tracking purposes.</li><li>Current status of flows for implementing these fields.</li><li>Conversation about creating new fields and analyzing field data for lead qualification.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>How critical is the ad set tracking for the team?</li><li>How to properly test the flows?</li><li>How to use Business Territory and Monthly Organic Traffic fields together to better qualify leads?</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Victor will speak with Victoria about the flows.</li><li>Bruna will need to test the flows thoroughly.</li><li>Victor will create a dashboard for quality assurance.</li><li>Bruna will analyze the difference between LES field and the newly implemented field.</li><li>Bruna will examine lead to DC conversion rates by Monthly Organic Traffic.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Discussion about ranges for Monthly Organic Traffic depending on Business Territory: local business &gt;250, and national &gt;500.</li></ul>',90,2,'2025-03-31 20:23:25.477228','2025-03-31 20:23:25.477228','2025-03-31',10);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(178,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>Discussion about expanding categorization of organic traffic sources.</li><li>Bruna added Tools which was missing, and "Verse Jazz" which is generating significant traffic.</li><li>Conversation about whether to include all tools under one category or separate them.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>How to categorize different tools (Ads Grader, Ubersuggest) in reporting?</li><li>Whether to split Ubersuggest into separate campaigns (onboarding, menu links, etc.) or keep them consolidated?</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Decision to keep tools categorization simpler for now by putting everything under "tools" category.</li><li>Bruna will look at marketing categorization to see what makes sense to add.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Different traffic sources from Ubersuggest discussed:&nbsp;<ul><li>Onboarding (when someone in free trial converts)</li><li>Menu links</li><li>Various other touchpoints that previously fell under "service consulting"</li></ul></li><li>UTM parameters allow tracking the specific source even within a single campaign.</li></ul>',88,2,'2025-03-31 20:25:22.654380','2025-03-31 20:25:22.654380','2025-03-31',10);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(179,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>Meta ads campaign had lower volume of Discovery Calls (DCs) in recent weeks.</li><li>Despite fewer DCs, several deals were closed from Meta, but most were from opportunities created in February, with only one from the current month.</li><li>Issues with paid ads included problems with creatives, pixel setup, extended learning phases, and budget adjustments.</li><li>"Unqualified" leads are affecting the intro to DC conversion.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>What exactly makes the leads unqualified? (Budget was mentioned as the main issue)</li><li>How to improve the quality of leads coming through paid channels?</li><li>How to handle the inconsistent budget management that led to overspending?</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>For April, the team decided not to change budgets on a daily basis to maintain campaign stability (Saulo).</li><li>Plans to narrow down audience targeting to be more effective and exclude non-converting groups (Saulo).</li><li>Will add new creatives in two weeks, aiming for steady volume of intros and DCs over the next 15 days (Saulo).</li><li>Need to assess performance of paid ads vendor after $1,500 overspend (Saulo).</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Conversion API for Meta has been fixed to help optimize for qualified pitches.</li><li>Despite high no-show rates perception, the actual no-show percentage was lower last week (11%) compared to previous weeks (15-32%).</li></ul>',82,2,'2025-03-31 20:27:49.066938','2025-03-31 20:27:49.066938','2025-03-31',1);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(180,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>Discussion about lead quality and qualification process.</li><li>For those who do show up, budget constraints were cited as the main reason for being unqualified.</li><li>Some intro calls are getting double-booked on calendars, which Bruna is investigating.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>How to reduce no-show rate for intro calls?</li><li>What qualification criteria should be applied to determine if a lead should move to DC stage?</li><li>How to resolve the double-booking issues with the calendar?</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Cody will provide more detailed statistics on intro call no-shows and reasons for disqualification.</li><li>Bruna is investigating the calendar double-booking issue.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>There seems to be a disconnect between initial reports of lead quality (Cody previously said intros were qualified if they answered) and current assessment (many are unqualified due to budget).</li></ul>',88,2,'2025-03-31 20:29:36.205329','2025-03-31 20:29:36.205329','2025-03-31',1);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(181,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>The team has made changes to forms to gather more data about leads, including monthly organic traffic.</li><li>Currently collecting data on potential qualification criteria but not yet using it for routing or queue management.</li><li>DC to pitch conversion rate was significantly higher than usual, especially for marketing campaign leads.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>What factors are contributing to the higher DC to pitch conversion?</li><li>When should the team start using the new qualification fields for lead routing?</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Continue collecting data on new form fields (monthly organic traffic, etc.) before implementing for qualification purposes.</li><li>Need deeper analysis to understand the increased DC to pitch conversion rate (Victor will have more to share in the retro).</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>The "work with us" form and quiz are generating significant numbers of qualified leads in the organic channel.</li></ul>',68,2,'2025-03-31 20:30:52.321508','2025-03-31 20:30:52.321508','2025-03-31',1);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(182,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>Overall positive results for the month with $126K in sales (on track to reach goal).</li><li>Marketing campaigns, particularly consulting emails, are generating consistent DCs that move to pitches, but some pitches aren''t converting on BOF.</li><li>Webinar performance varied - recent webinar didn''t perform well, but a previous one produced 9 pitches.</li><li>The team maintained a consistent average of $99K in monthly sales over the past two months.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>Why aren''t pitches from consulting emails converting at the expected rate?</li><li>How to improve webinar performance for lead generation?</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Expect 7-10 additional DCs from the upcoming webinar (Saulo).</li><li>Several open opportunities from the last successful webinar expected to carry over to April.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>The social media topic for the webinar didn''t perform as well as expected, which was surprising to the team.</li></ul>',87,2,'2025-03-31 20:33:49.241194','2025-03-31 20:33:49.241194','2025-03-31',1);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(183,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>The team discussed intro call performance from the previous week, with 28 sets completed.</li><li>There was a discrepancy in tracking no-shows due to issues with the no-show button in Salesforce following a Chili Piper migration.</li><li>Detailed analysis of paid intros showed 33 total scheduled, with 10 no-shows (30%) and 23 that actually happened.</li><li>Of the 23 that happened, only 2 were truly unqualified (one due to budget constraints, one non-English speaking).</li><li>The team confirmed that when leads show up to intro calls, they are generally qualified, suggesting the ad messaging is aligned with the company''s offerings: <a href="https://neilpateldigital-my.sharepoint.com/:x:/r/personal/codyh_npaccel_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=%7B304415C1-37FA-432D-BD0D-4E9E97FB29A7%7D&amp;file=Paid%20Intros%20-%20Week%20of%2024%20Mar.xlsx&amp;wdLOR=cD81F23AE-38AC-084F-AEBB-029F20EFC971&amp;fromShare=true&amp;action=default&amp;mobileredirect=true"><em>https://neilpateldigital-my.sharepoint.com/:x:/r/personal/codyh_npaccel_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=%7B304415C1-37FA-432D-BD0D-4E9E97FB29A7%7D&amp;file=Paid%20Intros%20-%20Week%20of%2024%20Mar.xlsx&amp;wdLOR=cD81F23AE-38AC-084F-AEBB-029F20EFC971&amp;fromShare=true&amp;action=default&amp;mobileredirect=true</em></a></li><li>Discussion about paid ad budget for April and expected intro volume.</li><li>Monday had 6 sets from paid sources, which is higher than usual for Mondays.</li><li>They saw 12 paid intros scheduled on Sunday, which was considered high.</li><li>The team expects around 30 - 35 paid intros per week in April based on the planned budget.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>How to standardize the process for marking no-shows (checkbox vs. button in Salesforce)?</li><li>How to improve the show rate for intro calls?</li><li>What will be the impact of the new monthly budget allocation on intro volume?</li><li>How to maintain a steady flow of intros without the fluctuations seen in March?</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Cody to send the detailed breakdown of intros to the marketing team.</li><li>Team to use the Chili Piper button in Salesforce for marking no-shows going forward (Bruno and Lindsay to follow up on removing the checkbox to avoid confusion).</li><li>Addressing the issue with Travis (BDR) who was using personal cell phone instead of Outreach for calls.</li><li>Budget for April has been approved and will be distributed steadily across the four weeks to avoid learning phase issues experienced previously.</li><li>Expected ~30 intros per week from paid channels in April, with slightly fewer in week 1 (around 25) and then 30-35 in the subsequent weeks.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Workable lead percentage is at 86% for the week, slightly down from the 91% average, but expected to increase.</li><li>Only one duplicate intro was identified, which was due to a timing issue where Chili Piper couldn''t detect it was the same email booking twice in rapid succession.</li></ul>',82,2,'2025-04-01 20:14:06.836452','2025-04-01 20:14:06.836452','2025-04-01',2);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(184,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>Detailed profitability analysis of the Meta paid ads channel was presented by Victor and Saulo.</li><li>In March, the campaign generated 6 paid deals with a performance ratio of 6.3x (Total Contract Value vs. Spend), approaching their target of 8x.</li><li>The Meta campaign contributed 8.6% of total company revenue over February and March, proving it''s a valuable new revenue channel.</li><li>Cumulative revenue from paid acquisition is approaching the 50% mark at 6 months.</li><li>March saw approximately 11k in MRR from this channel, with projected monthly recurring revenue reaching nearly 60k.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>How to improve the LTV/CAC ratio, which is currently at 1.4 (with a goal of at least 3)?</li><li>How to achieve more consistent results from the Meta ads channel?</li><li>How to optimize cost per pitch while maintaining conversion rates and average order value?</li><li>Whether to include headcount analysis in profitability calculations versus the current cost-per-call approach.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Discuss the headcount analysis approach and decide on a consistent presentation method for future meetings.</li><li>Working on filling the pipeline for April after successful February and March performance.</li><li>Continue to refine the profitability analysis to include more accurate churn data from this year''s cohort instead of using last year''s data.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Detailed breakdown of customer acquisition costs (CAC) included: contractor fees, marketing costs, call costs (intro, discovery, pitch), commission costs, and total ad spend.</li><li>Customers acquired through Meta ads have different metrics than business averages:&nbsp;<ul><li>Lower billing rate (68% vs 80% business average) due to churn</li><li>Lower cost of goods sold (41% vs 52% business average)</li><li>Higher customer acquisition cost (42% vs 35% business average)</li><li>Final margin is similar at around 43k</li></ul></li><li>Large number of "Level Up" deals contributed to the lower COGS for paid ad customers.</li><li>The team is focusing on analyzing cost per pitch in combination with pitch-to-deal conversion and average order value for a more complete picture.</li><li>Spreadsheet: <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/17fGECMJw-IfSQ9VFSjlJpnKsvYP3TYoTI6cOHdH_zjg/edit?pli=1&amp;gid=1503458276#gid=1503458276"><em>https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/17fGECMJw-IfSQ9VFSjlJpnKsvYP3TYoTI6cOHdH_zjg/edit?pli=1&amp;gid=1503458276#gid=1503458276</em></a></li></ul>',82,2,'2025-04-01 20:16:37.623127','2025-04-01 20:16:37.623127','2025-04-01',3);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(185,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>Discussion about expected weekly intro volume from paid ads for April (23-30 intros per week).</li><li>Current performance is on track with 14 intros in the first 3 days, projecting to reach 32 for the week.</li><li>Victor emphasized the need for consistency in the paid ads strategy, noting that the team has been making too many changes that result in campaigns spending too much time in learning phase.</li><li>Analysis of March performance showed most closed deals came from February opportunities, with only one from the current month.</li><li>Team discussed budget allocation approach for April to avoid continuous changes and learning phase issues.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>How to maintain consistent campaign performance without frequent creative or process changes?</li><li>How to improve lead quality from paid ads?</li><li>How to achieve a predictable volume of leads that would allow the team to calculate ROI on additional ad spend?</li><li>What type of messaging works best with the audiences and should be maintained?</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Maintain current budget allocation throughout April without significant changes to avoid learning phase issues (Saulo).</li><li>Continue monitoring performance of current messaging that appears to be resonating with qualified leads (Saulo/Victor).</li><li>Develop a profitability analysis that can be used to justify additional ad spend (Victor).</li><li>Work toward a more consistent approach to minimize "360-degree" changes in messaging or strategy.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Victor is concerned about frequent strategy shifts making it difficult to establish a consistent pipeline and reliable metrics.</li><li>The team reached 6.3x performance ratio (Total Contract Value vs. Spend) in March, approaching their target of 8x.</li><li>Paid campaigns contributed 8.6% of total revenue over February and March, establishing it as a valuable new revenue channel.</li><li>The team previously considered pausing the paid ads program during a difficult period, but the channel is now proving valuable.</li></ul>',82,2,'2025-04-02 19:26:36.641842','2025-04-02 19:26:36.641842','2025-04-02',6);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(186,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>Bruna reported a noticeable drop in lead volume across channels, particularly organic traffic.</li><li>Saulo analyzed the traffic data and found a 7-15% decrease in organic traffic compared to previous periods.</li><li>The team discovered an issue with Chili Piper routing, where leads with specific budget ranges were being incorrectly routed to AEs instead of BDRs.</li><li>Discussion about implementing a chat bot on the website as a new lead generation source.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>What is causing the decrease in organic traffic and lead volume?</li><li>How to fix the Chili Piper routing issue that''s affecting intro call scheduling?</li><li>How should the chat bot be implemented and integrated with current systems?</li><li>How should chat bot leads be categorized in analytics/reporting?</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Bruna to continue investigating the Chili Piper routing issue (already contacted support).</li><li>Hugo to implement a test version of the chat bot with the same form fields as the current website forms.</li><li>Bruna and Saulo to ensure the chat bot properly passes UTM parameters for attribution.</li><li>Saulo confirmed the chat bot leads should be categorized as organic traffic, with source attribution based on UTM parameters.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>The chat bot will initially be implemented on a test page.</li><li>The team will ensure the chat bot collects all the same fields as current forms, including newer fields like Monthly Organic Traffic and Business Territory.</li><li>The expectation is that the chat bot won''t significantly cannibalize other lead sources as it provides a different interactive experience.</li></ul>',88,2,'2025-04-02 19:30:07.737674','2025-04-02 19:30:07.737674','2025-04-02',6);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(187,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>Detailed analysis of lead quality based on new qualification fields (Monthly Organic Traffic and Business Territory).</li><li>Bruna presented data on lead distribution across different business categories and traffic volumes: <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1v-ebUEtRG_us2anHiqHLIY_u217-qw6n-DOtrHkNdAo/edit?gid=1468308639#gid=1468308639"><em>https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1v-ebUEtRG_us2anHiqHLIY_u217-qw6n-DOtrHkNdAo/edit?gid=1468308639#gid=1468308639</em></a></li><li>The team examined conversion rates from lead to discovery call based on these qualification criteria.</li><li>Discussion about whether current qualification thresholds are excluding potentially valuable leads.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>Are the current qualification thresholds for Monthly Organic Traffic and Business Territory appropriate?</li><li>How many qualified leads are being excluded by current routing rules?</li><li>Would including some currently excluded leads improve overall pipeline and conversion?</li><li>How to test whether the qualification criteria are working effectively?</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Saulo proposed testing the qualification criteria by routing some currently excluded leads to BDRs.</li><li>Bruna to further analyze the data, particularly for "International" businesses which showed interesting patterns.</li><li>Further analysis needed to examine the relationship between these qualification fields and actual deals closed.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Data showed many leads (83 for National businesses) are potentially qualified by traffic/territory criteria, but not proceeding to discovery calls.</li><li>The team found evidence that criteria like "I don''t have a business" are effectively identifying unqualified leads.</li><li>Discussion about whether leads with low traffic but budget availability might still be valuable customers.</li><li>Analysis covered data since March 19, when the qualification fields were implemented.</li></ul>',68,2,'2025-04-02 19:32:36.172064','2025-04-02 19:32:36.172064','2025-04-02',6);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(188,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>Discussion about upcoming webinars as a key lead generation channel, with analysis of past and future performance.</li><li>A recent webinar on "Social Media Secrets" underperformed with only 9 discovery calls (DCs) versus the goal of 20+.</li><li>Past webinars on SEO-related topics ("Future of Organic Traffic" and "Next Gen SEO") performed very well, with three deals closed.</li><li>Upcoming AI webinar "How to Get Mentioned in AI Overviews" scheduled for April 15th, with some debate about terminology that might be unfamiliar to prospects.</li><li>Team planning four webinars in April, including a special White Label webinar with David on April 22nd.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>How to improve marketing email clarity to prevent qualified leads from misunderstanding offers, especially for self-assessment focused emails (for this specifically, potentially test sending intros to BDRs since leads may have unreal expectations if messaging is not clear).</li><li>Whether to change "AI Overviews" terminology in webinar/emails title/materials to something more widely understood.</li><li>How to handle lead routing for the White Label webinar to ensure partnership leads go directly to David.</li><li>How to expand qualification criteria for the White Label webinar to include lower budget prospects ($750 and under).</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Barbara to add email subject lines to the tracking document to ensure clarity about self-assessment offers.</li><li>Team to consider routing self-assessment campaign responses to intro calls with BDRs first, rather than directly to AEs.</li><li>Hugo to add the team''s emails to all marketing email lists so everyone gets copies of outgoing communications.</li><li>Barbara to work with Hugo on White Label webinar routing to ensure leads are properly identified for David via UTM parameters.</li><li>Saulo to share 14 new ad scripts with the sales team for feedback before sending to Neil for approval and recording.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>The team discussed possibly making this meeting bi-weekly instead of monthly for more timely feedback, but noted scheduling challenges.</li><li>April 29th webinar will focus on paid media with "Google and Meta Ad Hacks That Work".</li><li>April email campaigns will focus on labor quality, ChatGPT traffic, content creation hacks, and a self-assessment guide.</li><li>Team plans to expand White Label webinar qualification criteria to include under $750 budget prospects.</li></ul>',94,2,'2025-04-03 17:25:59.465524','2025-04-03 17:58:04.841535','2025-04-03',3);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(189,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>Brief mention that the team is preparing 14 new ad scripts.</li><li>Saulo plans to share these scripts with the sales team for feedback before sending to Neil for approval and recording.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>How to improve collaboration between marketing and sales on ad messaging.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Saulo to circulate the 14 new ad scripts to the team for feedback before sending to Neil.</li><li>Team to prepare for the paid media webinar scheduled for April 29th.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>The process typically involves sending scripts directly to Neil for approval and recording, but Saulo wants to include the sales team''s perspective earlier in the process.</li></ul>',82,2,'2025-04-03 17:27:23.840891','2025-04-03 17:27:23.840891','2025-04-03',3);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(190,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>Nick and Victor analyzed March''s strong sales performance (126k) and discussed what made it successful and whether it''s replicable.</li><li>The team closed 42 deals in March, including 14 Level Up deals and 4 LBO deals.</li><li>Nick and Lindsay''s active involvement in pitches and follow-ups ("the Blitz") appeared to be a significant factor in closing more deals and improving conversion rates.</li><li>They discussed how "micromanaging" (active coaching, pitch preparation, and joining calls) helped even underperforming reps close deals.</li><li>Analysis of data showed approximately 30% of deals closed in March were from pitches held in February.</li><li>There was a notable increase in paid media deals (23 in total) compared to previous months.</li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li>Brief mention that the team sold 23 paid media deals in March (either standalone or as part of multi-product packages).</li><li>This represented a significant increase compared to previous months.</li><li>Paid media was included in some capacity in 50% of the 42 deals closed in March.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>Is the current approach with Nick and Lindsay joining pitches sustainable or will it lead to burnout?</li><li>How can Hannah (currently on leave) be effectively integrated into this process when she returns?</li><li>How should they measure "in-month" deals - by opportunity creation date or pitch held date?</li><li>What talent issues exist within the current sales team, and how should they be addressed?</li><li>How can they replicate March''s success in April without the pipeline rollover from February?</li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li>Why did paid media deals perform so well in March compared to previous months?</li><li>Is this performance repeatable or was it due to luck and specific market conditions?</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Continue the "Blitz" approach with Nick and Lindsay joining pitches and follow-ups.</li><li>Consider measuring "in-month" deals based on pitch held date rather than opportunity creation date for more accurate performance tracking.</li><li>Continue interviewing potential sales hires to address talent gaps (interview with a candidate from SEM Rush scheduled for Friday).</li><li>Work on transitioning Hannah into a role focused on pitch preparation and joining calls when she returns.</li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li>Potentially analyze which leads these paid media deals came from and what their declared marketing budgets were.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Nick identified talent tiers within the team: top performers (Mark Elkington, Jacob, David, Drew) who "get it" versus those who struggle (Spencer, Tim, and potentially Sadie).</li><li>Sadie was described as achieving results through volume rather than skill.</li><li>The "nine-block talent organization system" was discussed as a framework for evaluating sales reps based on performance and potential.</li><li>The team faces challenges with recruiting and hiring timeline issues that contributed to the current talent gaps.</li></ul>',87,2,'2025-04-03 17:34:21.442725','2025-04-03 17:36:31.222217','2025-04-03',5);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(191,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>Nick and Victor discussed talent gaps on the sales team as a key issue affecting performance.</li><li>The team is actively interviewing candidates, with Nick having conducted two interviews the previous day.</li><li>A promising candidate from SEM Rush is scheduled for an interview on Friday.</li><li>One candidate reached the final round of interviews, but was rejected for being "too rough around the edges" despite making it that far in the process.</li><li>Nick identified a clear distinction between high-performing reps (Mark Elkington, Jacob, David, Drew) and underperforming reps (Spencer, Tim, Sadie).</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>How to accelerate the hiring process to address critical talent gaps?</li><li>What specific qualities to look for in new hires (active listening, reading the room, intuition, coachability)?</li><li>How to determine if candidates have the necessary "intuition" and critical thinking skills?</li><li>Should they consider internal promotions to fill leadership roles?</li><li>How to balance immediate hiring needs with quality standards?</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Continue the interview process with the SEM Rush candidate (Nick).</li><li>Consider letting go of underperforming rep Tim to create space for new talent.</li><li>Evaluate internal candidates who might have leadership potential.</li><li>Clarify recruiting needs and process to avoid the previous 8-week delay when positions weren''t clearly defined.</li><li>Potentially involve Nick more directly in recruitment due to his understanding of what makes a successful sales rep.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>There appears to have been confusion about the recruitment process and how many reps were needed, which led to delays.</li><li>The team used the "nine-block talent organization system" to evaluate current reps based on performance and potential.</li><li>Mark Elkington was described as a "top performer without potential" (maximizing his capacity but resistant to change).</li><li>Jacob was characterized as a "top performer with potential" (strong results but still room to grow).</li><li>Drew was categorized as a "moderate performer with a ton of potential."</li><li>The team is concerned about the balance between team size and revenue targets - not having enough reps to hit goals but also needing to maintain quality standards.</li></ul>',93,2,'2025-04-03 17:53:21.166111','2025-04-03 17:53:21.166111','2025-04-03',3);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(192,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>Joe reported April is expected to be a difficult month for churn with current tracking at $118k, close to their re-forecasted target of $120k.</li><li>March performed well with approximately $102-103k in churn, better than expected.</li><li>Leadership team ("SLT") joined more client calls in March than ever before, which appears to have helped with client retention.</li><li>CS team has implemented several changes to control churn, including greater autonomy for Customer Success Managers to negotiate and offer free work.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>How to maintain the current momentum in churn prevention for April despite several known at-risk accounts.</li><li>Whether the high-touch approach with leadership joining calls is sustainable long-term.</li><li>Joe mentioned they''re "not winning back" a client he thought they had a good chance with - understanding why could be important.</li><li>Tracking active book of business is complex due to data being spread across manual spreadsheets and multiple systems.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Joe is focusing on winning back several pieces of canceled business to minimize April churn.</li><li>Victor is working with Victoria to explore solutions for untangling the complicated tracking system for active book of business.</li><li>Continue with the approach of offering strategic discounts and free work to retain valuable clients.</li><li>Maintain the "show of force" approach for accounts over $3,000, having directors and VPs join retention calls.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>There seems to be a correlation between good sales months and good retention months, possibly indicating broader market conditions or internal operational improvements.</li><li>The CS team is now more empowered to make decisions about discounts and free work to save clients - estimated at 2-3k of free work in some cases.</li><li>One $5k client (Bella Sarah) was retained primarily because leadership demonstrated they "clearly care about our business."</li><li>Joe mentioned they''re less concerned about retaining smaller accounts ($1,500 range) and focusing efforts on larger ones.</li></ul>',92,2,'2025-04-04 16:07:11.269777','2025-04-04 16:07:11.269777','2025-04-03',4);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(193,'<div><strong>Brief summary of what was discussed about this project in the meeting</strong></div><ul><li>Discussion about cancellation of a scheduled email for a Partner webinar that was set for 8:00 am PST.</li><li>The cancellation was due to the need to align how leads from this partner webinar would be delivered to David.</li><li>Currently, no changes have been made in the systems (LeanData and ChiliPiper), meaning all leads would be routed to BDRs normally.</li><li>Leads above $750 that don''t schedule meetings would be added to the Webinar sequence.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions to be answered or problems/blockers/concerns to be solved/addressed to move this project forward</strong></div><ul><li>Whether to route partner leads to Sam (current setup) or David (would require removing Sam from LeanData routing).</li><li>Which budget levels of scheduled meetings David should receive.</li><li>How to handle leads that don''t schedule meetings - whether they should enter the same Outreach sequence for partners from live webinar.</li><li>The number of alignments and system changes needed make it challenging to implement immediately.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Bruna will align directly with David and make the necessary changes with Hugo.</li><li>The email will be rescheduled for next Tuesday instead of the original date.</li><li>Another email will be sent on Friday as previously agreed with Hugo Coelho.</li><li>The team needs to test any changes made to the systems before sending the email</li><li><br></li></ul><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Current routing logic sends leads to different calendars based on budget:&nbsp;<ul><li>$750 - $1,500: BDR calendar</li><li>$1,500 - $50,000: NPA AE calendar</li><li>Above $50,000: NPD AE calendar</li></ul></li><li>There are no more available users within LeanData, and partner leads