--------------------------------------------------</div><div><br></div><div>-&gt; <strong>TOP 3 INSIGHTS FROM FUNNELS</strong></div><ul><li>Decrease of leads, Intros and DCs are the main issues (more details in the NPA Sales Leadership Channel)</li><li>Highest No Show rate in the last 8 weeks = 42%, specially on Setter DCs = 50%</li><li>Marketing campaigns, specially consulting and content aren''t performing as it should</li></ul>',99,3,'2025-04-15 22:20:33.842196','2025-04-15 22:25:18.815844','2025-04-14',10);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(246,'<div><strong>Webinars &amp; Email Promotionals</strong></div><ul><li>discussing dc''s, pitches and mrr pacing for the month for the different types of mkt campaigns (see screenshots 1 to 3)</li><li>review/discuss past and upcoming webinars. documentation <a href="https://neilpateldigital.sharepoint.com/:x:/s/NPAMarketing/EZQSzgzgn3NaPW4_brsSbbYBapfTphgAQ5N_ZQLVncmikQ?e=dGgJ5s&amp;%3D&amp;sdata=SzVUVkcvZkt1YWFESE14dlBwdlhRWnNzVDVZVGgxUHhmdU42c3pEWi9tST0%3D&amp;ovuser=50ec670c-3c36-4537-9af7-2f7fbe49b769%2Cvictork%40npaccel.com"><em>here</em></a></li><li>review/discuss this and next week''s promotional emails. documentation <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1qAX7Y2SH-LiW-Blo0oHoHBB-0N7xoonbWT1YVycKeIU/edit?tab=t.q51zhe28w7fh#heading=h.s1faw98a986h"><em>here</em></a></li></ul><div><br></div><div>&nbsp;<strong>Meta Paid Acquisition</strong></div><ul><li>discussing dc''s, pitches and mrr pacing for the month for the different types of mkt campaigns (see screenshots 4)</li><li>currently pacing to 81 total intros this month and 2 deals. with current conversions and aov, would get us to 3.8k in mrr, usually expect revenue from new business sales between 10-15k (for npa)</li><li>beginning of april expectation was to generate ~30 intros per week + increase in budget to ~30k&nbsp;<ul><li>&nbsp;actual intro performance:&nbsp;<ul><li>2 weeks ago: 26 intros</li><li>last week: 20 intros</li><li>currently: 11 intros</li><li>projected this week: 29 based on L8W avg</li></ul></li><li>dc performance from paid acquisition:&nbsp;<ul><li>2 weeks ago: 14 dcs</li><li>last week: 10 dcs</li><li>this week: 13 dcs</li><li>projected this week: 9 based on L8W avg</li><li>key question: why aren''t we seeing the expected increase? what creatives are currently active with more budget allocated?</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><div><br></div>',99,3,'2025-04-15 22:37:32.726748','2025-04-16 10:49:33.876507','2025-04-16',2);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(248,'<div><strong>Brief summary</strong>&nbsp;</div><ul><li>The meeting involved discussion about sales team performance issues, particularly around their approach to sales calls, value-based selling, and the lack of proper storytelling to address client pain points. Joe shared insights about how sales reps aren''t effectively connecting solutions to client problems.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Sales team not effectively articulating the value proposition and telling a complete story from pain point to solution</li><li>Some sales reps (particularly legacy reps like Tim) lack deep product knowledge, making it difficult to build trust with prospects</li><li>Lack of consistent coaching and call reviews to improve sales performance</li><li>New product packages (creative packages) were rolled out but sales team wasn''t properly informed despite being on the call</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible</strong></div><ul><li>Need for better coaching of sales reps to improve value-based selling approach</li><li>Sales management should implement more call reviews using Clari AI to identify improvement areas</li><li>Improve communication about new product offerings to the sales team</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Joe presented an example of effective client communication from a Halo meeting where they discussed strategy, methodology, performance comparisons, and future partnership plans</li><li>The team currently holds unsustainable "blitz" approach where managers join every pitch and follow-up call rather than building rep capabilities</li><li>There appear to be coaching sessions happening, but unclear if they''re effective or focused on the right things</li></ul>',87,3,'2025-04-17 14:06:04.128810','2025-04-17 14:06:04.128810','2025-04-15',4);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(249,'<div><strong>Brief summary</strong></div><ul><li>Discussion about issues with the handover process between sales and account management, identifying it as part of a broader communication problem rather than an isolated issue.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Handover problems stem from insufficient information collection during discovery and pitch phases</li><li>Sales not discovering enough about clients'' pain points to properly brief account managers</li><li>Lack of value-based selling makes handovers difficult because there''s little meaningful information to transfer</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible</strong></div><ul><li>Need to improve the discovery and pitch process to collect better information that can be handed over</li><li>Develop a more structured handover approach that focuses on client pain points and prescribed solutions</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Joe believes the handover is "a small piece of a bigger issue" related to sales approach</li><li>The account management side is trying to improve storytelling and demonstrating value to clients</li></ul>',80,3,'2025-04-17 14:12:12.794406','2025-04-17 14:12:12.794406','2025-04-15',4);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(250,'<div><strong>Brief summary</strong></div><ul><li>Victor and Joe briefly discussed talent issues on the sales team and the lack of a proper recruiting pipeline.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Lack of a consistent hiring pipeline for sales positions</li><li>Some underperforming legacy sales representatives that may need replacement</li><li>Not proactively interviewing candidates on a regular basis</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible</strong></div><ul><li>Need to establish a consistent pipeline of sales candidates similar to how they manage sales leads</li><li>Should be interviewing potential sales reps regularly rather than reactively</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Victor mentioned the team interviewed "a few reps" last month, but suggested this isn''t sufficient</li><li>Victor believes they don''t have a talent issue so much as a hiring process issue</li></ul>',93,3,'2025-04-17 14:13:05.909025','2025-04-17 14:13:05.909025','2025-04-15',4);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(251,'<div><strong>Brief summary</strong>&nbsp;</div><ul><li>Information about an analysis regarding client risk profiles and industry categorization during economic uncertainty.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Trying to understand which client industries might be more susceptible to economic downturns</li><li>Segmenting clients based on risk factors like industry, size, and capital reserves</li><li>Understanding difference between new business and existing clients in terms of retention risk</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible</strong></div><ul><li>Continue monitoring client performance across different segments</li><li>Maintain awareness of economic indicators that might affect client acquisition and retention</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Risk analysis showing potential revenue impact if clients reduced spending by 10%, 20%, or 50%</li><li>Identified that new business acquisition is more vulnerable than existing client retention</li><li>Noted that existing clients who have seen performance are more likely to stay during economic uncertainty</li><li>Market volatility in early April (6,000 point drop) may have temporarily frozen decision-making for prospects</li></ul>',92,3,'2025-04-17 14:14:22.876461','2025-04-17 14:14:22.876461','2025-04-15',4);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(252,'<div><strong>Brief summary</strong></div><ul><li>The meeting focused on improving the contract sending process and establishing clear criteria for when contracts should be sent to prospects. They also discussed current pipeline challenges, with low pitches and contracts being a concern for the month.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Contract to deal conversion rate is too low, indicating contracts are being sent prematurely</li><li>Sales reps are sending contracts without confirming key information</li><li>Current forecast has been reduced to 100 due to light opportunity pipeline</li><li>Low pitch volume (19 last week compared to 35-38 in previous periods)</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible</strong></div><ul><li>Implementation of 3 key qualification questions before sending contracts: 1) Do you know the signer/decision maker? 2) Do you have clear established next steps? 3) Did you finalize pricing?</li><li>Prepare examples from Clari of contracts sent without proper qualification</li><li>Team to accept that implementing these criteria may reduce contract numbers, but improve conversion rates</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Contract-to-deal conversion rate in previous company was 99%, while the current team''s rate is much lower</li><li>The team has $40K in contract sent and $32K in proposal stage currently</li><li>3 qualification criteria to be asked for every opportunity during pipeline reviews (part of the agenda)</li></ul>',87,3,'2025-04-17 14:16:40.401072','2025-04-17 14:16:40.401072','2025-04-15',11);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(253,'<div><strong>Brief summary</strong>&nbsp;</div><ul><li>Discussion about low discovery call quality leading to fewer pitches, and the practice of having multiple team members on sales calls to build trust and value.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>DC quality is low, which is affecting pitch conversion</li><li>Organic lead volume is down</li><li>Holding Marketing accountable for why meta intros are down</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible</strong></div><ul><li>Team to continue monitoring DC quality and its impact on pitch conversions</li><li>8 pitches scheduled for today</li><li>Team to evaluate whether having multiple people on calls (including Will and Lindsay) is helping build trust</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>The team discussed that bringing others on calls, even if they don''t participate much, can help build trust and add perceived value</li><li>There was discussion about whether this practice might undermine the trust in salespeople themselves</li><li>Lindsay noted that this approach varies in effectiveness depending on the sales rep (better for stronger reps like Mark, Drew, Jacob; more problematic for weaker reps like Tim)</li></ul>',88,3,'2025-04-17 14:22:25.499781','2025-04-17 14:22:25.499781','2025-04-16',11);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(254,'<div><strong>Brief summary</strong></div><ul><li>Brief discussion about a recent webinar that generated a good number of discovery calls, and plans to review upcoming webinars and email campaigns.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Marketing campaigns and organic channels are both underperforming</li><li>Need to focus on future webinars and email campaigns to improve performance</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible</strong></div><ul><li>Review email copies and documentation together in an upcoming meeting</li><li>Discuss upcoming webinars, including a recent partners webinar that generated many SQLs in an upcoming meeting as well</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>A partners webinar generated approximately 200 SQLs, but not direct DCs because David chose to follow up with leads himself</li><li>There appears to be a plan to implement a similar approach to the monthly sales and marketing alignment meeting to review email and webinar performance</li></ul>',94,3,'2025-04-17 14:23:48.389740','2025-04-17 14:23:48.389740','2025-04-16',11);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(255,'<div><strong>Brief summary</strong>&nbsp;</div><ul><li>Holding Marketing accountable on the paid acquisition funnel</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Meta intros are down. Need to understand why</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible</strong></div><ul><li>Discuss why meta intros are down</li><li>Team to evaluate what can be done with webinar and email promotions to make up for the drop</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Outbound prospecting has been deprioritized due to being short two managers and focusing on hiring and backfilling positions</li><li>There was discussion about potentially lower market demand affecting lead volume</li><li>The forecast for the month has been reduced to 100 (presumably $100K)</li><li>The team is implementing a new meeting format combining two previous meetings, which Sarah supports</li></ul>',82,3,'2025-04-17 14:25:15.049440','2025-04-17 14:25:15.049440','2025-04-16',11);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(256,'<div><strong>Brief summary</strong>&nbsp;</div><ul><li>The meeting focused on reviewing webinar performance, upcoming webinar plans, and email marketing strategies. They discussed a recent AI-focused webinar that had 15 DCs so far and an upcoming white label partner webinar being launched next week.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>How to improve email marketing performance and copy to increase conversions</li><li>Need for better tracking of partner webinar leads and making sure they''re properly qualified</li><li>Determining the right process for handling white label partner leads that register for the webinar</li><li>Lack of urgency in email copy for Monday promotional emails</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible</strong></div><ul><li>David to send questions today for a pre-webinar survey to qualify white label partner leads</li><li>Bruna to adjust Outreach sequence by removing Sam''s booking link from emails as well as changing the process for the white label partners webinar:<ul><li>previously, david requested that all leads or mqls signing up for the webinar were routed directly to him without booking options.</li><li>now he wants these leads routed to all bdrs like any other lead source. bdrs will qualify them through the sequence and book the discovery call with david.</li></ul></li><li>Cody to have BDRs make first calls to the white label webinar leads for qualification</li><li>Lindsay, Nick, and David to review email copy by end of day and provide feedback</li><li>David to join a BDR training session on Monday to prepare them for qualifying white label leads</li><li>David to create supporting documents for BDRs about the white label partnership program</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>The "How to get mentioned in AI search results" webinar has generated 15 DCs so far with a goal of 20 (prob won''t generate any other DCs, as typically 66% of webinar DCs come before the event and 34% after)</li><li>The white label partners webinar has collected around 200 leads already</li><li>The team will pre-record the webinar on Monday morning and run it live on Tuesday</li><li>David and the team will monitor the chat during the live webinar broadcast</li></ul>',94,3,'2025-04-17 14:51:32.591212','2025-04-17 14:51:32.591212','2025-04-16',2);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(257,'<div><strong>Brief summary</strong>&nbsp;</div><ul><li>Discussion about the performance of paid ads, with a focus on improving intro calls and addressing unqualified leads issues.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Intros from paid are below target (goal was 30 per week, but only getting 18-26)</li><li>Need to optimize budget and creative performance</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible</strong></div><ul><li>Several optimizations: removing underperforming AI-related ads, emphasizing spend on search everywhere optimization creative</li><li>Implementation of new lookalike audience for search everywhere optimization</li><li>Feeding Meta with offline conversions data from people who purchased services since beginning of the year</li><li>Team creating new ad creatives focused on pain points and holistic marketing perspective</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Despite lower performance, there are signs of improvement with 18 intros this week (as of Wednesday) compared to 20 for all of last week</li><li>With budget increases, the target should be 40-43 intros for the current week</li><li>Exploring new creative formats, including a quiz-style approach</li></ul>',82,3,'2025-04-17 14:52:58.386109','2025-04-17 14:52:58.386109','2025-04-16',2);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(258,'<div><strong>Brief summary</strong></div><ul><li>Discussion about routing and managing white label partner webinar leads, including changes to Outreach sequences and BDR qualification processes.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Current Outreach sequence has Sam''s booking link which needs to be changed</li><li>Need for proper qualification of white label partner leads before they reach David</li><li>How to remove leads from sequences after David makes manual contact</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible</strong></div><ul><li>Bruna to adjust Outreach sequence by removing Sam''s booking link from emails as well as changing the process for the white label partners webinar:<ul><li>previously, david requested that all leads or mqls signing up for the webinar were routed directly to him without booking options.</li><li>now he wants these leads routed to all bdrs like any other lead source. bdrs will qualify them through the sequence and book the discovery call with david.</li></ul></li><li>Cody to have BDRs make first calls to the white label webinar leads for qualification</li><li>Bruna to rotate leads to all BDRs instead of routing directly to David</li><li>David to manually remove leads from sequences if he contacts them outside of Outreach</li><li>Cody to ensure BDRs make first calls to move leads through the sequence properly</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>David is receiving notifications for all MQLs from the white label webinar</li><li>The team is considering a pre-webinar survey to help prioritize leads</li><li>BDRs will qualify leads first and then schedule qualified ones with David</li></ul>',98,3,'2025-04-17 14:54:21.812522','2025-04-17 14:54:21.812522','2025-04-16',2);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(259,'<div><strong>Brief summary</strong>&nbsp;</div><ul><li>Discussion about lead generation strategies, including email campaigns targeted at different segments and under-budget leads.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Discovery calls are pacing well but pitch conversion is low</li><li>Different types of email campaigns (Monday standalone emails, Tuesday content, Wednesday consulting) performing differently</li><li>Opportunity to re-engage under-budget leads</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible</strong></div><ul><li>Team to review and improve email copy for the Monday "Content Creation Hacks" campaign</li><li>Team to discuss DC quality and pitch conversion in next meeting</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Monday emails go to a highly segmented list (from Hubspot, meaning above budget, US division, etc) of about 100,000 people with target budgets</li><li>A special campaign for under-budget leads aims to get them to re-qualify with higher budgets</li><li>The team closed a deal last month from the under-budget campaign</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information (not related to any specific project)</strong></div><ul><li>David suggested potentially exploring a referral program for existing clients, but was told this would need to be discussed with Joe and Matt</li><li>The team implemented a new Wednesday meeting format to discuss marketing performance and strategies</li><li>Webinar platform is being changed, which may affect how the team manages chat during live broadcasts</li></ul>',88,3,'2025-04-17 14:56:41.875063','2025-04-17 14:56:41.875063','2025-04-16',2);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(260,'<ul><li>12 intros scheduled yesterday (L8W avg for wednesdays was at 3, considering the last couple of weeks where volume was lower).</li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li>for the week, we''re now at 28, potentially pacing to low 40s, which is great. let’s see how they convert to DCs and down funnel metrics. these are the ad ids that generated the most intros during yesterday''s spike, can you share the links to the creatives, pls?<ul><li>6697660358233</li><li>6677078398833</li><li>6698071919033</li></ul></li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li>after a couple weeks of low performance, we''re now at 29 intros this week and hopefully will reach low 40s. this should help make up for previous lower volume and start filling the pipeline again.</li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li>not sure if revenue will come in april, but if we maintain this pace, we should start may with a strong pipeline from this channel specifically</li></ul>',82,3,'2025-04-17 15:10:36.554402','2025-04-17 16:47:37.971133','2025-04-17',3);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(261,'<ul><li>we want to compare what people are putting in forms with the information pulled automatically from the lead enrichment system. we''re still iterating and haven''t reached a conclusion yet.</li></ul><div><br></div><ul><li>potential next steps:<ul><li>potentially switch LES to pull traffic info from semrush instead of current platform</li><li>compare data points again</li><li>if too different again, use semrush as potential source of truth</li></ul></li></ul>',68,3,'2025-04-17 15:29:03.561427','2025-04-17 15:29:03.561427','2025-04-17',3);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(262,'<div><strong>Brief summary</strong>&nbsp;</div><ul><li>Discussion focused on alarming trends in the sales pipeline, particularly the low pitch volume and conversion rates. The team is seeing significantly lower DC to pitch conversion (45% in April compared to 75-77% in February/March), affecting the ability to close deals this month.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Low pitch volume due to DC quality issues and high no-show rates (43% last week)</li><li>DC to pitch conversion is at the lowest level since December 2023 (excluding seasonal variations)</li><li>Several top performers (Mark Elkington, Sadie, David) have zero or minimal sales this month</li><li>Pipeline for May is concerning due to current low pitch volume</li><li>Forecast has been lowered to $100K (down from original target)</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible</strong></div><ul><li>Nick to pull data on DCs by rep and determine reasons for low conversion to pitches</li><li>Nick to research whether specific reps have contributed to the lower conversion rates</li><li>Nick working on reinventing the DC and pitch evaluation process with standardized feedback</li><li>Lindsay planning to roll out new contract sending rules on Monday</li><li>Nick to follow up with Mark Elkington about his low pipeline and conversion rates</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Contract to deal conversion is still at 52%, which is acceptable for this point in the month</li><li>Some reps showing unusual patterns - typically lower performers (Tim, Spencer) are at the top while strong performers are struggling</li><li>Only 4 of 14 closed deals this month had pitches held in April, showing high reliance on older opportunities</li><li>Nick believes DC quality issues stem from market uncertainty and economic concerns affecting prospects</li><li>Top performing rep Jacob closed $28K last month but is at risk of missing targets this month</li></ul>',87,3,'2025-04-17 18:13:14.621915','2025-04-17 18:13:14.621915','2025-04-17',5);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(263,'<div><strong>Brief summary</strong>&nbsp;</div><ul><li>Discussion about lower quality discovery calls and high no-show rates affecting the sales pipeline. Both quality and volume of DCs are concerning, with many prospects showing confusion about what they scheduled or looking for services outside the company''s offerings.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Many prospects seem confused about what the discovery call is for when contacted</li><li>Significant number of unqualified DCs (prospects looking for web design, which is a deal breaker)</li><li>High no-show rates last week (43%) affecting pitch volume</li><li>Many prospects bringing up economic concerns during calls</li><li>Quality issues reported by key reps like Mark Elkington</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible</strong></div><ul><li>Nick to listen to some DC recordings to identify patterns in quality issues</li><li>Nick considering more involvement in DCs to help improve conversion rates</li><li>Nick developing a more standardized DC outline/evaluation process</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Monthly no-show rates (27% April, 29% March, 32% February, 31% January) show some improvement</li><li>Nick shared an example of a DC that seemed qualified but couldn''t move forward because the prospect''s website was controlled by their current agency</li><li>Several prospects mentioned economic concerns, market conditions, and reluctance to commit to contracts</li></ul>',88,3,'2025-04-17 18:14:00.860340','2025-04-17 18:14:00.860340','2025-04-17',5);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(264,'<div><strong>Brief summary</strong>&nbsp;</div><ul><li>Brief discussion about the challenging hiring process and the higher standards being applied to new sales candidates.</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main questions/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>HR is sourcing more candidates but many are unqualified</li><li>Interview process taking up time on Nick''s calendar</li><li>Team has raised standards for hiring based on current successful reps</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible</strong></div><ul><li>Nick to review list of candidates and potentially expedite screening</li><li>Continuing to maintain higher standards despite hiring needs</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Recent interviews have resulted in many rejections due to higher standards</li><li>Nick, Lindsay, and Santos appear aligned on raising the quality bar for new hires</li><li>Experience with previous hires showing that training cannot overcome fundamental skill/aptitude gaps</li></ul>',93,3,'2025-04-17 18:15:12.289312','2025-04-17 18:15:12.289312','2025-04-17',5);
