INSERT INTO comments VALUES(302,'<div><strong>Brief summary of the discussion</strong></div><ul><li>Discussion about integrating a form/questionnaire flow for Ubersuggest and Answer the Public tools that connects qualified leads to the agency</li><li>The flow includes a quiz-like questionnaire that collects user information and, for qualified leads, shows calendar booking options</li><li>Team is working on embedding the Chili Piper calendar and setting up connections to HubSpot and Salesforce</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main problems/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Need to determine the complete set of fields to include in the onboarding questionnaire</li><li>Question about whether to include standard form fields (marketing team size, monthly organic traffic) in the flow to avoid users filling out multiple forms</li><li>Need to establish conditional logic so only qualified leads (US-based with marketing budget over $1500) see the calendar booking option</li><li>Team unsure if they can implement the calendar embedding immediately</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Luisa to continue building the flow without the calendar booking feature initially</li><li>Caio to send a screenshot of the existing consulting page form to ensure alignment of fields</li><li>Team to implement the form with proper connections to HubSpot and Salesforce first</li><li>Luisa to work on adding conditional logic to show booking options only to qualified leads</li><li>Tsunoda to provide documentation for HubSpot endpoint integration (already sent email Friday)</li><li>Luis and team to coordinate with Tsunoda via Teams chat for technical implementation details</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>The same flow will be used for both Ubersuggest and Answer the Public tools</li><li>The form will collect basic information including email, website URL, location, phone number, and monthly marketing budget</li><li>Calendar booking options should only appear for US-based users with marketing budgets over $1500</li><li>The flow will include multiple service options, with some directing users to calendar booking</li></ul>',104,2,'2025-05-20 17:30:36.060466','2025-05-20 17:30:36.060466','2025-05-19',3);
INSERT INTO comments VALUES(303,'<div><strong>Brief summary of the discussion</strong></div><ul><li>Discussion about updating metrics in the dashboard/report with new terminology and measurement points</li><li>Team is refining how to track the sales funnel stages more accurately with terms like "DC happening," "pitch prep," and "pitch held"</li><li>Need to update summary views and forecasting reports with the new metrics</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main problems/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Ensuring proper historical tracking as some metrics only have data from February onwards</li><li>Need to determine how to represent the data in month-over-month reporting for metrics that don''t have historical data</li><li>Figuring out how to incorporate the new metrics into the summary dashboard</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Implement the agreed funnel steps: "DC scheduled" → "DC no show" → "DC happening" → "pitch prep" → "pitch held" → "contract"</li><li>Add the new metrics to the summary view, focusing on volume rather than conversion rates</li><li>Add cohort analysis for "DC happening to pitch" as an unofficial but insightful metric</li><li>Determine how to represent missing historical data in month-over-month views (using dashes or zeros)</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>"DC happening to pitch" conversion appears to be a key bottleneck in the sales funnel</li><li>Sales team needs to address why DCs aren''t converting to pitches</li><li>The volume of DCs has returned to previous levels, but conversion remains an issue</li></ul>',96,2,'2025-05-20 17:34:49.110658','2025-05-20 17:34:49.110658','2025-05-19',10);
