INSERT INTO comments VALUES(307,'<div><strong>Brief summary of the discussion</strong></div><ul><li>Discussion about implementing a form for Ubersuggest and Answer the Public (ATP) to collect leads for BDR cold outreach</li><li>Originally there was consideration of adding a Chili Piper calendar booking option, but decided to start with just the form first</li><li>The team is developing a sequence for these leads, including calls and emails</li><li>This implementation aims to address the dip in organic traffic and leads</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main problems/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Lack of clarity on exactly when the form will go live (Caio is pushing for immediate implementation)</li><li>BDRs haven''t been trained yet on how to handle these leads</li><li>Previous attempts at working with ATP leads had poor conversion rates</li><li>Concern about the potentially high volume of leads from ATP overwhelming BDRs</li><li>Uncertainty whether the form will be implemented for account creation (high volume) or onboarding (lower volume)</li><li>Leads may not recognize MP Digital or Neil Patel when called</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>Victor to create a group chat with Bruna, Salo, and Caio to clarify implementation details</li><li>Cody to prepare BDR team and provide training (Wednesday at the latest)</li><li>Cody to review and implement the email sequence that''s been created</li><li>Bruna to help finalize the emails for the sequence</li><li>Team to determine whether to segment ATP leads separately in reporting to avoid skewing conversion metrics</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Neil views this as a potential "saving grace" to replace the dip in organic traffic</li><li>The team previously attempted working with ATP leads with limited success</li><li>The UK team has an email-only ATP sequence in outreach</li><li>Team plans to have a