INSERT INTO comments VALUES(308,'<div><strong>Brief summary of the discussion</strong></div><ul><li>Team reviewed the current sales pipeline and discussed active opportunities</li><li>Current pipeline shows $45,000 closed MTD with $6,000 in commit, $32,000 in contracts, and $54,000 in proposals</li><li>Team is tracking toward around 90% of $100K goal for the month</li><li>Momentum is picking up with 24 pitches scheduled for the week</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Main problems/blockers/concerns</strong></div><ul><li>Main funnel gap identified is in DC to pitch conversion</li><li>Several deals have stalled or been pushed to June</li><li>Some prospects have gone silent or are difficult to reach</li><li>Concern about potential impact of the upcoming long weekend on deal closing</li><li>Trending toward more paid-only pitches (vs. SEO), potentially due to AI impact on organic traffic</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Next steps and who is responsible for it</strong></div><ul><li>David to follow up on Roadrunner deal that''s been stalled</li><li>David to move Q deals to June forecast based on funding delays</li><li>Jacob and David working on following up with several potential deals this week</li><li>Lindsay to investigate why DCs aren''t converting to pitches and provide qualitative feedback</li><li>Team to continue following up on outstanding proposals and opportunities</li></ul><div><br></div><div><strong>Additional Information</strong></div><ul><li>Several specific deals were discussed including Watershep, Roman Dental, Roadrunner, Blue Gems, TSK Tiger Shulman</li><li>Team is seeing an increase in paid-only pitches, potentially as clients pivot away from SEO due to AI impact</li><li>Noticing more DIY-minded prospects who want information but may not be ready to hire an agency</li><li>Jacob and David working on updating the pricing presentation for paid services to avoid the appearance of bait-and-switch</li></ul>',87,2,'2025-05-20 17:45:37.702371','2025-05-20